32 // Each concrete ElementsAccessor can handle exactly one ElementsKind,
33 // several abstract ElementsAccessor classes are used to allow sharing
34 // common code.
35 //
36 // Inheritance hierarchy:
37 // - ElementsAccessorBase (abstract)
38 // - FastElementsAccessor (abstract)
39 // - FastSmiOrObjectElementsAccessor
40 // - FastPackedSmiElementsAccessor
41 // - FastHoleySmiElementsAccessor
42 // - FastPackedObjectElementsAccessor
43 // - FastNonextensibleObjectElementsAccessor: template
44 // - FastPackedNonextensibleObjectElementsAccessor
45 // - FastHoleyNonextensibleObjectElementsAccessor
46 // - FastSealedObjectElementsAccessor: template
47 // - FastPackedSealedObjectElementsAccessor
48 // - FastHoleySealedObjectElementsAccessor
49 // - FastFrozenObjectElementsAccessor: template
50 // - FastPackedFrozenObjectElementsAccessor
51 // - FastHoleyFrozenObjectElementsAccessor
52 // - FastHoleyObjectElementsAccessor
53 // - FastDoubleElementsAccessor
54 // - FastPackedDoubleElementsAccessor
55 // - FastHoleyDoubleElementsAccessor
56 // - TypedElementsAccessor: template, with instantiations:
57 // - Uint8ElementsAccessor
58 // - Int8ElementsAccessor
59 // - Uint16ElementsAccessor
60 // - Int16ElementsAccessor
61 // - Uint32ElementsAccessor
62 // - Int32ElementsAccessor
63 // - Float32ElementsAccessor
64 // - Float64ElementsAccessor
65 // - Uint8ClampedElementsAccessor
66 // - BigUint64ElementsAccessor
67 // - BigInt64ElementsAccessor
68 // - RabGsabUint8ElementsAccessor
69 // - RabGsabInt8ElementsAccessor
70 // - RabGsabUint16ElementsAccessor
71 // - RabGsabInt16ElementsAccessor
72 // - RabGsabUint32ElementsAccessor
73 // - RabGsabInt32ElementsAccessor
74 // - RabGsabFloat32ElementsAccessor
75 // - RabGsabFloat64ElementsAccessor
76 // - RabGsabUint8ClampedElementsAccessor
77 // - RabGsabBigUint64ElementsAccessor
78 // - RabGsabBigInt64ElementsAccessor
79 // - DictionaryElementsAccessor
80 // - SloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor
81 // - FastSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor
82 // - SlowSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor
83 // - StringWrapperElementsAccessor
84 // - FastStringWrapperElementsAccessor
85 // - SlowStringWrapperElementsAccessor

92 #define RETURN_NOTHING_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(call) \
93  do { \
94  if (!(call)) return Nothing<bool>(); \
95  } while (false)
96 
97 #define RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(call) \
98  do { \
99  ExceptionStatus status_enum_result = (call); \
100  if (!status_enum_result) return status_enum_result; \
101  } while (false)

107 // First argument in list is the accessor class, the second argument is the
108 // accessor ElementsKind, and the third is the backing store class. Use the
109 // fast element handler for smi-only arrays. The implementation is currently
110 // identical. Note that the order must match that of the ElementsKind enum for
111 // the |accessor_array[]| below to work.
112 #define ELEMENTS_LIST(V) \
113  V(FastPackedSmiElementsAccessor, PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
114  V(FastHoleySmiElementsAccessor, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
115  V(FastPackedObjectElementsAccessor, PACKED_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
116  V(FastHoleyObjectElementsAccessor, HOLEY_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
117  V(FastPackedDoubleElementsAccessor, PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, \
118  FixedDoubleArray) \
119  V(FastHoleyDoubleElementsAccessor, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, FixedDoubleArray) \
120  V(FastPackedNonextensibleObjectElementsAccessor, \
121  PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
122  V(FastHoleyNonextensibleObjectElementsAccessor, \
123  HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
124  V(FastPackedSealedObjectElementsAccessor, PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS, \
125  FixedArray) \
126  V(FastHoleySealedObjectElementsAccessor, HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
127  V(FastPackedFrozenObjectElementsAccessor, PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS, \
128  FixedArray) \
129  V(FastHoleyFrozenObjectElementsAccessor, HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
130  V(SharedArrayElementsAccessor, SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS, FixedArray) \
131  V(DictionaryElementsAccessor, DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS, NumberDictionary) \
132  V(FastSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor, FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS, \
133  FixedArray) \
134  V(SlowSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor, SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS, \
135  FixedArray) \
136  V(FastStringWrapperElementsAccessor, FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS, \
137  FixedArray) \
138  V(SlowStringWrapperElementsAccessor, SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS, \
139  FixedArray) \
140  V(Uint8ElementsAccessor, UINT8_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
141  V(Int8ElementsAccessor, INT8_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
142  V(Uint16ElementsAccessor, UINT16_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
143  V(Int16ElementsAccessor, INT16_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
144  V(Uint32ElementsAccessor, UINT32_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
145  V(Int32ElementsAccessor, INT32_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
146  V(BigUint64ElementsAccessor, BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
147  V(BigInt64ElementsAccessor, BIGINT64_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
148  V(Uint8ClampedElementsAccessor, UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
149  V(Float32ElementsAccessor, FLOAT32_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
150  V(Float64ElementsAccessor, FLOAT64_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
151  V(Float16ElementsAccessor, FLOAT16_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
152  V(RabGsabUint8ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_UINT8_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
153  V(RabGsabInt8ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_INT8_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
154  V(RabGsabUint16ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_UINT16_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
155  V(RabGsabInt16ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_INT16_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
156  V(RabGsabUint32ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_UINT32_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
157  V(RabGsabInt32ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_INT32_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
158  V(RabGsabBigUint64ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
159  V(RabGsabBigInt64ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_BIGINT64_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
160  V(RabGsabUint8ClampedElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS, \
161  ByteArray) \
162  V(RabGsabFloat32ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_FLOAT32_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
163  V(RabGsabFloat64ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_FLOAT64_ELEMENTS, ByteArray) \
164  V(RabGsabFloat16ElementsAccessor, RAB_GSAB_FLOAT16_ELEMENTS, ByteArray)

166 template <ElementsKind Kind>
167 class ElementsKindTraits {
168  public:
169  using BackingStore = FixedArrayBase;
170 };
171 
172 #define ELEMENTS_TRAITS(Class, KindParam, Store) \
173  template <> \
174  class ElementsKindTraits<KindParam> { \
175  public: /* NOLINT */ \
176  static constexpr ElementsKind Kind = KindParam; \
177  using BackingStore = Store; \
178  }; \
179  constexpr ElementsKind ElementsKindTraits<KindParam>::Kind;
180 ELEMENTS_LIST(ELEMENTS_TRAITS)
181 #undef ELEMENTS_TRAITS

188 WriteBarrierMode GetWriteBarrierMode(Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements,
189  ElementsKind kind,
190  const DisallowGarbageCollection& promise) {
191  if (IsSmiElementsKind(kind)) return SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER;
192  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) return SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER;
193  return elements->GetWriteBarrierMode(promise);
194 }
195 
196 // If kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole is specified as the copy_size to
197 // CopyElements, it copies all of elements from source after source_start to
198 // destination array, padding any remaining uninitialized elements in the
199 // destination array with the hole.
200 constexpr int kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole = -1;
201 
202 void CopyObjectToObjectElements(Isolate* isolate,
203  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from_base,
204  ElementsKind from_kind, uint32_t from_start,
205  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to_base,
206  ElementsKind to_kind, uint32_t to_start,
207  int raw_copy_size) {
208  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
209  DCHECK(to_base->map() != roots.fixed_cow_array_map());
210  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
211  int copy_size = raw_copy_size;
212  if (raw_copy_size < 0) {
213  DCHECK_EQ(kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole, raw_copy_size);
214  copy_size = std::min(from_base->length() - from_start,
215  to_base->length() - to_start);
216  int start = to_start + copy_size;
217  int length = to_base->length() - start;
218  if (length > 0) {
219  MemsetTagged(Cast<FixedArray>(to_base)->RawFieldOfElementAt(start),
220  roots.the_hole_value(), length);
221  }
222  }
223  DCHECK((copy_size + static_cast<int>(to_start)) <= to_base->length() &&
224  (copy_size + static_cast<int>(from_start)) <= from_base->length());
225  if (copy_size == 0) return;
226  Tagged<FixedArray> from = Cast<FixedArray>(from_base);
227  Tagged<FixedArray> to = Cast<FixedArray>(to_base);
228  DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(from_kind));
229  DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(to_kind));
230 
231  WriteBarrierMode write_barrier_mode =
232  (IsObjectElementsKind(from_kind) && IsObjectElementsKind(to_kind))
233  ? UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER
234  : SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER;
235  to->CopyElements(isolate, to_start, from, from_start, copy_size,
236  write_barrier_mode);
237 }
238 
239 void CopyDictionaryToObjectElements(Isolate* isolate,
240  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from_base,
241  uint32_t from_start,
242  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to_base,
243  ElementsKind to_kind, uint32_t to_start,
244  int raw_copy_size) {
245  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
246  Tagged<NumberDictionary> from = Cast<NumberDictionary>(from_base);
247  int copy_size = raw_copy_size;
248  if (raw_copy_size < 0) {
249  DCHECK_EQ(kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole, raw_copy_size);
250  copy_size = from->max_number_key() + 1 - from_start;
251  int start = to_start + copy_size;
252  int length = to_base->length() - start;
253  if (length > 0) {
254  MemsetTagged(Cast<FixedArray>(to_base)->RawFieldOfElementAt(start),
255  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).the_hole_value(), length);
256  }
257  }
258  DCHECK(to_base != from_base);
259  DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(to_kind));
260  if (copy_size == 0) return;
261  Tagged<FixedArray> to = Cast<FixedArray>(to_base);
262  uint32_t to_length = to->length();
263  if (to_start + copy_size > to_length) {
264  copy_size = to_length - to_start;
265  }
266  WriteBarrierMode write_barrier_mode = GetWriteBarrierMode(to, to_kind, no_gc);
267  for (int i = 0; i < copy_size; i++) {
268  InternalIndex entry = from->FindEntry(isolate, i + from_start);
269  if (entry.is_found()) {
270  Tagged<Object> value = from->ValueAt(entry);
271  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(value, isolate));
272  to->set(i + to_start, value, write_barrier_mode);
273  } else {
274  to->set_the_hole(isolate, i + to_start);
275  }
276  }
277 }
278 
279 // NOTE: this method violates the handlified function signature convention:
280 // raw pointer parameters in the function that allocates.
281 // See ElementsAccessorBase::CopyElements() for details.
282 void CopyDoubleToObjectElements(Isolate* isolate,
283  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from_base,
284  uint32_t from_start,
285  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to_base,
286  uint32_t to_start, int raw_copy_size) {
287  int copy_size = raw_copy_size;
288  if (raw_copy_size < 0) {
289  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
290  DCHECK_EQ(kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole, raw_copy_size);
291  copy_size = std::min(from_base->length() - from_start,
292  to_base->length() - to_start);
293  // Also initialize the area that will be copied over since HeapNumber
294  // allocation below can cause an incremental marking step, requiring all
295  // existing heap objects to be properly initialized.
296  int start = to_start;
297  int length = to_base->length() - start;
298  if (length > 0) {
299  MemsetTagged(Cast<FixedArray>(to_base)->RawFieldOfElementAt(start),
300  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).the_hole_value(), length);
301  }
302  }
303 
304  DCHECK((copy_size + static_cast<int>(to_start)) <= to_base->length() &&
305  (copy_size + static_cast<int>(from_start)) <= from_base->length());
306  if (copy_size == 0) return;
307 
308  // From here on, the code below could actually allocate. Therefore the raw
309  // values are wrapped into handles.
310  DirectHandle<FixedDoubleArray> from(Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(from_base),
311  isolate);
312  DirectHandle<FixedArray> to(Cast<FixedArray>(to_base), isolate);
313 
314  // Use an outer loop to not waste too much time on creating HandleScopes.
315  // On the other hand we might overflow a single handle scope depending on
316  // the copy_size.
317  int offset = 0;
318  while (offset < copy_size) {
319  HandleScope scope(isolate);
320  offset += 100;
321  for (int i = offset - 100; i < offset && i < copy_size; ++i) {
322  DirectHandle<Object> value =
323  FixedDoubleArray::get(*from, i + from_start, isolate);
324  to->set(i + to_start, *value, UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
325  }
326  }
327 }
328 
329 void CopyDoubleToDoubleElements(Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from_base,
330  uint32_t from_start,
331  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to_base,
332  uint32_t to_start, int raw_copy_size) {
333  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
334  int copy_size = raw_copy_size;
335  if (raw_copy_size < 0) {
336  DCHECK_EQ(kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole, raw_copy_size);
337  copy_size = std::min(from_base->length() - from_start,
338  to_base->length() - to_start);
339  for (int i = to_start + copy_size; i < to_base->length(); ++i) {
340  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base)->set_the_hole(i);
341  }
342  }
343  DCHECK((copy_size + static_cast<int>(to_start)) <= to_base->length() &&
344  (copy_size + static_cast<int>(from_start)) <= from_base->length());
345  if (copy_size == 0) return;
346  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> from = Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(from_base);
347  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> to = Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base);
348  Address to_address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(to->begin());
349  Address from_address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(from->begin());
350  to_address += kDoubleSize * to_start;
351  from_address += kDoubleSize * from_start;
352 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
353  // TODO(ishell, v8:8875): we use CopyTagged() in order to avoid unaligned
354  // access to double values in the arrays. This will no longed be necessary
355  // once the allocations alignment issue is fixed.
356  int words_per_double = (kDoubleSize / kTaggedSize);
357  CopyTagged(to_address, from_address,
358  static_cast<size_t>(words_per_double * copy_size));
359 #else
360  int words_per_double = (kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize);
361  CopyWords(to_address, from_address,
362  static_cast<size_t>(words_per_double * copy_size));
363 #endif
364 }
365 
366 void CopySmiToDoubleElements(Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from_base,
367  uint32_t from_start,
368  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to_base, uint32_t to_start,
369  int raw_copy_size) {
370  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
371  int copy_size = raw_copy_size;
372  if (raw_copy_size < 0) {
373  DCHECK_EQ(kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole, raw_copy_size);
374  copy_size = from_base->length() - from_start;
375  for (int i = to_start + copy_size; i < to_base->length(); ++i) {
376  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base)->set_the_hole(i);
377  }
378  }
379  DCHECK((copy_size + static_cast<int>(to_start)) <= to_base->length() &&
380  (copy_size + static_cast<int>(from_start)) <= from_base->length());
381  if (copy_size == 0) return;
382  Tagged<FixedArray> from = Cast<FixedArray>(from_base);
383  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> to = Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base);
384  Tagged<Object> the_hole = GetReadOnlyRoots().the_hole_value();
385  for (uint32_t from_end = from_start + static_cast<uint32_t>(copy_size);
386  from_start < from_end; from_start++, to_start++) {
387  Tagged<Object> hole_or_smi = from->get(from_start);
388  if (hole_or_smi == the_hole) {
389  to->set_the_hole(to_start);
390  } else {
391  to->set(to_start, Smi::ToInt(hole_or_smi));
392  }
393  }
394 }

396 void CopyPackedSmiToDoubleElements(Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from_base,
397  uint32_t from_start,
398  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to_base,
399  uint32_t to_start, int packed_size,
400  int raw_copy_size) {
401  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
402  int copy_size = raw_copy_size;
403  uint32_t to_end;
404  if (raw_copy_size < 0) {
405  DCHECK_EQ(kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole, raw_copy_size);
406  copy_size = packed_size - from_start;
407  to_end = to_base->length();
408  for (uint32_t i = to_start + copy_size; i < to_end; ++i) {
409  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base)->set_the_hole(i);
410  }
411  } else {
412  to_end = to_start + static_cast<uint32_t>(copy_size);
413  }
414  DCHECK(static_cast<int>(to_end) <= to_base->length());
415  DCHECK(packed_size >= 0 && packed_size <= copy_size);
416  DCHECK((copy_size + static_cast<int>(to_start)) <= to_base->length() &&
417  (copy_size + static_cast<int>(from_start)) <= from_base->length());
418  if (copy_size == 0) return;
419  Tagged<FixedArray> from = Cast<FixedArray>(from_base);
420  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> to = Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base);
421  for (uint32_t from_end = from_start + static_cast<uint32_t>(packed_size);
422  from_start < from_end; from_start++, to_start++) {
423  Tagged<Object> smi = from->get(from_start);
424  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(smi));
425  to->set(to_start, Smi::ToInt(smi));
426  }
427 }

429 void CopyObjectToDoubleElements(Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from_base,
430  uint32_t from_start,
431  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to_base,
432  uint32_t to_start, int raw_copy_size) {
433  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
434  int copy_size = raw_copy_size;
435  if (raw_copy_size < 0) {
436  DCHECK_EQ(kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole, raw_copy_size);
437  copy_size = from_base->length() - from_start;
438  for (int i = to_start + copy_size; i < to_base->length(); ++i) {
439  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base)->set_the_hole(i);
440  }
441  }
442  DCHECK((copy_size + static_cast<int>(to_start)) <= to_base->length() &&
443  (copy_size + static_cast<int>(from_start)) <= from_base->length());
444  if (copy_size == 0) return;
445  Tagged<FixedArray> from = Cast<FixedArray>(from_base);
446  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> to = Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base);
447  Tagged<Hole> the_hole = GetReadOnlyRoots().the_hole_value();
448  for (uint32_t from_end = from_start + copy_size; from_start < from_end;
449  from_start++, to_start++) {
450  Tagged<Object> hole_or_object = from->get(from_start);
451  if (hole_or_object == the_hole) {
452  to->set_the_hole(to_start);
453  } else {
454  to->set(to_start, Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(hole_or_object)));
455  }
456  }
457 }

459 void CopyDictionaryToDoubleElements(Isolate* isolate,
460  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from_base,
461  uint32_t from_start,
462  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to_base,
463  uint32_t to_start, int raw_copy_size) {
464  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
465  Tagged<NumberDictionary> from = Cast<NumberDictionary>(from_base);
466  int copy_size = raw_copy_size;
467  if (copy_size < 0) {
468  DCHECK_EQ(kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole, copy_size);
469  copy_size = from->max_number_key() + 1 - from_start;
470  for (int i = to_start + copy_size; i < to_base->length(); ++i) {
471  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base)->set_the_hole(i);
472  }
473  }
474  if (copy_size == 0) return;
475  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> to = Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(to_base);
476  uint32_t to_length = to->length();
477  if (to_start + copy_size > to_length) {
478  copy_size = to_length - to_start;
479  }
480  for (int i = 0; i < copy_size; i++) {
481  InternalIndex entry = from->FindEntry(isolate, i + from_start);
482  if (entry.is_found()) {
483  to->set(i + to_start,
484  Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(from->ValueAt(entry))));
485  } else {
486  to->set_the_hole(i + to_start);
487  }
488  }
489 }

491 void SortIndices(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<FixedArray> indices,
492  uint32_t sort_size) {
493  if (sort_size == 0) return;
494 
495  // Use AtomicSlot wrapper to ensure that std::sort uses atomic load and
496  // store operations that are safe for concurrent marking.
497  AtomicSlot start(indices->RawFieldOfFirstElement());
498  AtomicSlot end(start + sort_size);
499  std::sort(start, end, [isolate](Tagged_t elementA, Tagged_t elementB) {
500 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
501  Tagged<Object> a(V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(elementA));
502  Tagged<Object> b(V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(elementB));
503 #else
504  Tagged<Object> a(elementA);
505  Tagged<Object> b(elementB);
506 #endif
507  if (IsSmi(a) || !IsUndefined(a, isolate)) {
508  if (!IsSmi(b) && IsUndefined(b, isolate)) {
509  return true;
510  }
511  return Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(a)) <
512  Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(b));
513  }
514  return !IsSmi(b) && IsUndefined(b, isolate);
515  });
516  WriteBarrier::ForRange(isolate->heap(), *indices, ObjectSlot(start),
517  ObjectSlot(end));
518 }
519 
520 Maybe<bool> IncludesValueSlowPath(Isolate* isolate,
521  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
522  DirectHandle<Object> value, size_t start_from,
523  size_t length) {
524  bool search_for_hole = IsUndefined(*value, isolate);
525  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
526  LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, k);
527  if (!it.IsFound()) {
528  if (search_for_hole) return Just(true);
529  continue;
530  }
531  DirectHandle<Object> element_k;
532  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, element_k,
533  Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
534 
535  if (Object::SameValueZero(*value, *element_k)) return Just(true);
536  }
537 
538  return Just(false);
539 }
540 
541 Maybe<int64_t> IndexOfValueSlowPath(Isolate* isolate,
542  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
543  DirectHandle<Object> value,
544  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
545  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
546  LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, k);
547  if (!it.IsFound()) {
548  continue;
549  }
550  DirectHandle<Object> element_k;
551  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
552  isolate, element_k, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<int64_t>());
553 
554  if (Object::StrictEquals(*value, *element_k)) return Just<int64_t>(k);
555  }
556 
557  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
558 }
559 
560 // The InternalElementsAccessor is a helper class to expose otherwise protected
561 // methods to its subclasses. Namely, we don't want to publicly expose methods
562 // that take an entry (instead of an index) as an argument.
563 class InternalElementsAccessor : public ElementsAccessor {
564  public:
565  InternalIndex GetEntryForIndex(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder,
566  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
567  size_t index) override = 0;
568 
569  PropertyDetails GetDetails(Tagged<JSObject> holder,
570  InternalIndex entry) override = 0;
571 };
572 
573 // Base class for element handler implementations. Contains the
574 // the common logic for objects with different ElementsKinds.
575 // Subclasses must specialize method for which the element
576 // implementation differs from the base class implementation.
577 //
578 // This class is intended to be used in the following way:
579 //
580 // class SomeElementsAccessor :
581 // public ElementsAccessorBase<SomeElementsAccessor,
582 // BackingStoreClass> {
583 // ...
584 // }
585 //
586 // This is an example of the Curiously Recurring Template Pattern (see
587 // http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curiously_recurring_template_pattern). We use
588 // CRTP to guarantee aggressive compile time optimizations (i.e. inlining and
589 // specialization of SomeElementsAccessor methods).
590 template <typename Subclass, typename ElementsTraitsParam>
591 class ElementsAccessorBase : public InternalElementsAccessor {
592  public:
593  ElementsAccessorBase() = default;
594  ElementsAccessorBase(const ElementsAccessorBase&) = delete;
595  ElementsAccessorBase& operator=(const ElementsAccessorBase&) = delete;
596 
597  using ElementsTraits = ElementsTraitsParam;
598  using BackingStore = typename ElementsTraitsParam::BackingStore;
599 
600  static ElementsKind kind() { return ElementsTraits::Kind; }
601 
602  static void ValidateContents(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder,
603  size_t length) {}
604 
605  static void ValidateImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder) {
606  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> fixed_array_base = holder->elements();
607  if (!IsHeapObject(fixed_array_base)) return;
608  // Arrays that have been shifted in place can't be verified.
609  if (IsFreeSpaceOrFiller(fixed_array_base)) return;
610  size_t length = 0;
611  if (IsJSArray(holder)) {
612  Tagged<Object> length_obj = Cast<JSArray>(holder)->length();
613  if (IsSmi(length_obj)) {
614  length = Smi::ToInt(length_obj);
615  }
616  } else if (IsJSTypedArray(holder)) {
617  length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(holder)->GetLength();
618  } else {
619  length = fixed_array_base->length();
620  }
621  Subclass::ValidateContents(isolate, holder, length);
622  }
623 
624  void Validate(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder) final {
625  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
626  Subclass::ValidateImpl(isolate, holder);
627  }
628 
629  bool HasElement(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder, uint32_t index,

633  filter);

815  Maybe<bool> SetLength(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSArray> array,

820 
821  static void DecreaseLength(Isolate* isolate,
822  Tagged<BackingStore> backing_store,
823  uint32_t old_length, uint32_t length) {
824  uint32_t capacity = backing_store->capacity();
825  // It's possible we got here through left-trimming, which would have reduced
826  // the capacity.
827  if (V8_UNLIKELY(2 * length + JSObject::kMinAddedElementsCapacity <=
828  capacity)) {
829  // If more than half the elements won't be used, trim the array.
830  // Do not trim from short arrays to prevent frequent trimming on
831  // repeated pop operations.
832  // Leave some space to allow for subsequent push operations.
833  uint32_t new_capacity =
834  length + 1 == old_length ? (capacity + length) / 2 : length;
835  DCHECK_LT(new_capacity, capacity);
836  isolate->heap()->RightTrimArray(backing_store, new_capacity, capacity);
837  capacity = new_capacity;
838  }
839  }
840 
841  static Maybe<bool> SetLengthImpl(Isolate* isolate,
842  DirectHandle<JSArray> array, uint32_t length,
843  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
844  DCHECK(!array->SetLengthWouldNormalize(length));
845  DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(array->GetElementsKind()));
846  uint32_t old_length = 0;
847  CHECK(Object::ToArrayIndex(array->length(), &old_length));
848 
849  if (old_length < length) {
850  ElementsKind kind = array->GetElementsKind();
851  if (!IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
852  kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(kind);
853  JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(isolate, array, kind);
854  }
855  }
856 
857  // Check whether the backing store should be shrunk or grown.
858  uint32_t capacity = backing_store->length();
859  old_length = std::min(old_length, capacity);
860  if (length == 0) {
861  array->initialize_elements();
862  } else if (length <= capacity) {
863  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind())) {
864  JSObject::EnsureWritableFastElements(isolate, array);
865  if (array->elements() != *backing_store) {
866  backing_store = direct_handle(array->elements(), isolate);
867  }
868  }
869  DecreaseLength(isolate, Cast<BackingStore>(*backing_store), old_length,
870  length);
871  // Fill the non-trimmed elements with holes.
872  // Also use min if we don't RightTrim. It's possible we got here through
873  // left-trimming.
874  capacity = backing_store->length();
875  Cast<BackingStore>(*backing_store)
876  ->FillWithHoles(length, std::min(old_length, capacity));
877  } else {
878  // Calculate a new capacity for the array.
879  uint32_t new_capacity;
880  if (capacity == 0) {
881  // If the existing capacity is zero, assume we are setting the length to
882  // presize to the exact size we want.
883  new_capacity = length;
884  } else {
885  // Otherwise, assume we want exponential growing semantics, and grow as
886  // if we were pushing. We might not grow enough for the length, so take
887  // the max of hte two values.
888  new_capacity = std::max(length, JSArray::NewElementsCapacity(capacity));
889  }
890  // Grow the array to the new capacity. Note that this code will allow
891  // create backing stores that consist almost entirely of holes, for which
892  // `JSObject::ShouldConvertToSlowElements` would return "true". This is
893  // intentional, because we are assuming the user is setting a length to
894  // pre-size an array to then write to it within bounds. A subsequent
895  // resizing operation, like Array.p.push, might still trigger a transition
896  // to dictionary elements because of sparseness.
897  MAYBE_RETURN(
898  Subclass::GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(isolate, array, new_capacity),
899  Nothing<bool>());
900  }
901 
902  array->set_length(Smi::FromInt(length));
903  JSObject::ValidateElements(isolate, *array);
904  return Just(true);
905  }
906

909  receiver->elements());

934  static MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> ConvertElementsWithCapacity(
935  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
936  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> old_elements, ElementsKind from_kind,
937  uint32_t capacity) {
938  return ConvertElementsWithCapacity(isolate, object, old_elements, from_kind,
939  capacity, 0, 0);
940  }
941 
942  static MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> ConvertElementsWithCapacity(
943  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
944  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> old_elements, ElementsKind from_kind,
945  uint32_t capacity, uint32_t src_index, uint32_t dst_index) {
946  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> new_elements;
947  // TODO(victorgomes): Retrieve native context in optimized code
948  // and remove the check isolate->context().is_null().
949  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind())) {
950  if (!isolate->context().is_null() &&
951  !base::IsInRange(capacity, 0, FixedDoubleArray::kMaxLength)) {
952  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
953  NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength));
954  }
955  new_elements = isolate->factory()->NewFixedDoubleArray(capacity);
956  } else {
957  if (!isolate->context().is_null() &&
958  !base::IsInRange(capacity, 0, FixedArray::kMaxLength)) {
959  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
960  NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength));
961  }
962  new_elements = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(capacity);
963  }
964 
965  int packed_size = kPackedSizeNotKnown;
966  if (IsFastPackedElementsKind(from_kind) && IsJSArray(*object)) {
967  packed_size = Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(*object)->length());
968  }
969 
970  Subclass::CopyElementsImpl(isolate, *old_elements, src_index, *new_elements,
971  from_kind, dst_index, packed_size,
972  kCopyToEndAndInitializeToHole);
973 
974  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArrayBase>(new_elements);
975  }
976 
977  static void TransitionElementsKindImpl(Isolate* isolate,
978  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
979  DirectHandle<Map> to_map) {
980  DirectHandle<Map> from_map(object->map(), isolate);
981  ElementsKind from_kind = from_map->elements_kind();
982  ElementsKind to_kind = to_map->elements_kind();
983  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(from_kind)) {
984  to_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(to_kind);
985  }
986  if (from_kind != to_kind) {
987  // This method should never be called for any other case.
988  DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(from_kind));
989  DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(to_kind));
990  DCHECK_NE(TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, from_kind);
991 
992  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> from_elements(object->elements(), isolate);
993  if (object->elements() == ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array() ||
994  IsDoubleElementsKind(from_kind) == IsDoubleElementsKind(to_kind)) {
995  // No change is needed to the elements() buffer, the transition
996  // only requires a map change.
997  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, to_map);
998  } else {
999  DCHECK(
1000  (IsSmiElementsKind(from_kind) && IsDoubleElementsKind(to_kind)) ||
1001  (IsDoubleElementsKind(from_kind) && IsObjectElementsKind(to_kind)));
1002  uint32_t capacity = static_cast<uint32_t>(object->elements()->length());
1003  // Since the max length of FixedArray and FixedDoubleArray is the same,
1004  // we can safely assume that element conversion with the same capacity
1005  // will succeed.
1006  static_assert(FixedArray::kMaxLength == FixedDoubleArray::kMaxLength);
1007  DCHECK_LE(capacity, FixedArray::kMaxLength);
1008  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements =
1009  ConvertElementsWithCapacity(isolate, object, from_elements,
1010  from_kind, capacity)
1011  .ToHandleChecked();
1012  JSObject::SetMapAndElements(isolate, object, to_map, elements);
1013  }
1014  if (v8_flags.trace_elements_transitions) {
1015  JSObject::PrintElementsTransition(
1016  stdout, object, from_kind, from_elements, to_kind,
1017  direct_handle(object->elements(), isolate));
1018  }
1019  }
1020  }
1021 
1022  static Maybe<bool> GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(Isolate* isolate,
1023  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1024  uint32_t capacity) {
1025  ElementsKind from_kind = object->GetElementsKind();
1026  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(from_kind)) {
1027  // Array optimizations rely on the prototype lookups of Array objects
1028  // always returning undefined. If there is a store to the initial
1029  // prototype object, make sure all of these optimizations are invalidated.
1030  isolate->UpdateNoElementsProtectorOnSetLength(object);
1031  }
1032  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> old_elements(object->elements(), isolate);
1033  // This method should only be called if there's a reason to update the
1034  // elements.
1035  DCHECK(IsDoubleElementsKind(from_kind) != IsDoubleElementsKind(kind()) ||
1036  IsDictionaryElementsKind(from_kind) ||
1037  static_cast<uint32_t>(old_elements->length()) < capacity);
1038  return Subclass::BasicGrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(
1039  isolate, object, old_elements, from_kind, kind(), capacity);
1040  }
1041 
1042  static Maybe<bool> BasicGrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(
1043  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1044  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> old_elements, ElementsKind from_kind,
1045  ElementsKind to_kind, uint32_t capacity) {
1046  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements;
1047  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1048  isolate, elements,
1049  ConvertElementsWithCapacity(isolate, object, old_elements, from_kind,
1050  capacity),
1051  Nothing<bool>());
1052 
1053  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(from_kind)) {
1054  to_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(to_kind);
1055  }
1056  DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
1057  JSObject::GetElementsTransitionMap(isolate, object, to_kind);
1058  JSObject::SetMapAndElements(isolate, object, new_map, elements);
1059 
1060  // Transition through the allocation site as well if present.
1061  JSObject::UpdateAllocationSite(isolate, object, to_kind);
1062 
1063  if (v8_flags.trace_elements_transitions) {
1064  JSObject::PrintElementsTransition(stdout, object, from_kind, old_elements,
1065  to_kind, elements);
1066  }
1067  return Just(true);
1068  }
1069 
1070  void TransitionElementsKind(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1071  DirectHandle<Map> map) final {
1072  Subclass::TransitionElementsKindImpl(isolate, object, map);
1073  }
1074 
1075  Maybe<bool> GrowCapacityAndConvert(Isolate* isolate,
1076  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1077  uint32_t capacity) final {
1078  return Subclass::GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(isolate, object, capacity);
1079  }
1080 
1081  Maybe<bool> GrowCapacity(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1082  uint32_t index) final {
1083  // This function is intended to be called from optimized code. We don't
1084  // want to trigger lazy deopts there, so refuse to handle cases that would.
1085  if (object->map()->is_prototype_map() ||
1086  object->WouldConvertToSlowElements(index)) {
1087  return Just(false);
1088  }
1089  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> old_elements(object->elements(), isolate);
1090  uint32_t new_capacity = JSObject::NewElementsCapacity(index + 1);
1091  DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(old_elements->length()) < new_capacity);
1092  static_assert(FixedArray::kMaxLength == FixedDoubleArray::kMaxLength);
1093  constexpr uint32_t kMaxLength = FixedArray::kMaxLength;
1094 
1095  if (new_capacity > kMaxLength) {
1096  return Just(false);
1097  }
1098  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements;
1099  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1100  isolate, elements,
1101  ConvertElementsWithCapacity(isolate, object, old_elements, kind(),
1102  new_capacity),
1103  Nothing<bool>());
1104 
1105  DCHECK_EQ(object->GetElementsKind(), kind());
1106  // Transition through the allocation site as well if present.
1107  if (JSObject::UpdateAllocationSite<AllocationSiteUpdateMode::kCheckOnly>(
1108  isolate, object, kind())) {
1109  return Just(false);
1110  }
1111 
1112  object->set_elements(*elements);
1113  return Just(true);
1114  }
1115 
1116  void Delete(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
1117  InternalIndex entry) final {
1118  Subclass::DeleteImpl(isolate, obj, entry);
1119  }
1120 
1121  static void CopyElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from,
1122  uint32_t from_start, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to,
1123  ElementsKind from_kind, uint32_t to_start,
1124  int packed_size, int copy_size) {
1125  UNREACHABLE();
1126  }
1127 
1128  void CopyElements(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> from_holder,
1129  uint32_t from_start, ElementsKind from_kind,
1130  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> to, uint32_t to_start,
1131  int copy_size) final {
1132  int packed_size = kPackedSizeNotKnown;
1133  bool is_packed =
1134  IsFastPackedElementsKind(from_kind) && IsJSArray(from_holder);
1135  if (is_packed) {
1136  packed_size = Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(from_holder)->length());
1137  if (copy_size >= 0 && packed_size > copy_size) {
1138  packed_size = copy_size;
1139  }
1140  }
1141  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from = from_holder->elements();
1142  // NOTE: the Subclass::CopyElementsImpl() methods
1143  // violate the handlified function signature convention:
1144  // raw pointer parameters in the function that allocates. This is done
1145  // intentionally to avoid ArrayConcat() builtin performance degradation.
1146  //
1147  // Details: The idea is that allocations actually happen only in case of
1148  // copying from object with fast double elements to object with object
1149  // elements. In all the other cases there are no allocations performed and
1150  // handle creation causes noticeable performance degradation of the builtin.
1151  Subclass::CopyElementsImpl(isolate, from, from_start, *to, from_kind,
1152  to_start, packed_size, copy_size);
1153  }
1154 
1155  void CopyElements(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> source,
1156  ElementsKind source_kind,
1157  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> destination,
1158  int size) override {
1159  Subclass::CopyElementsImpl(isolate, *source, 0, *destination, source_kind,
1160  0, kPackedSizeNotKnown, size);
1161  }

1199 
1200  Maybe<bool> CollectValuesOrEntries(Isolate* isolate,
1201  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1202  DirectHandle<FixedArray> values_or_entries,
1203  bool get_entries, int* nof_items,
1204  PropertyFilter filter) override {
1205  return Subclass::CollectValuesOrEntriesImpl(
1206  isolate, object, values_or_entries, get_entries, nof_items, filter);
1207  }
1208 
1209  static Maybe<bool> CollectValuesOrEntriesImpl(
1210  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1211  DirectHandle<FixedArray> values_or_entries, bool get_entries,
1212  int* nof_items, PropertyFilter filter) {
1213  DCHECK_EQ(*nof_items, 0);
1214  KeyAccumulator accumulator(isolate, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
1215  ALL_PROPERTIES);
1216  RETURN_NOTHING_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(Subclass::CollectElementIndicesImpl(
1217  object, direct_handle(object->elements(), isolate), &accumulator));
1218  DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys = accumulator.GetKeys();
1219 
1220  int count = 0;
1221  int i = 0;
1222  ElementsKind original_elements_kind = object->GetElementsKind();
1223 
1224  for (; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
1225  DirectHandle<Object> key(keys->get(i), isolate);
1226  uint32_t index;
1227  if (!Object::ToUint32(*key, &index)) continue;
1228 
1229  DCHECK_EQ(object->GetElementsKind(), original_elements_kind);
1230  InternalIndex entry = Subclass::GetEntryForIndexImpl(
1231  isolate, *object, object->elements(), index, filter);
1232  if (entry.is_not_found()) continue;
1233  PropertyDetails details = Subclass::GetDetailsImpl(*object, entry);
1234 
1235  DirectHandle<Object> value;
1236  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
1237  value = Subclass::GetInternalImpl(isolate, object, entry);
1238  } else {
1239  // This might modify the elements and/or change the elements kind.
1240  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, index, LookupIterator::OWN);
1241  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1242  isolate, value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
1243  }
1244  if (get_entries) value = MakeEntryPair(isolate, index, value);
1245  values_or_entries->set(count++, *value);
1246  if (object->GetElementsKind() != original_elements_kind) break;
1247  }
1248 
1249  // Slow path caused by changes in elements kind during iteration.
1250  for (; i < keys->length(); i++) {
1251  DirectHandle<Object> key(keys->get(i), isolate);
1252  uint32_t index;
1253  if (!Object::ToUint32(*key, &index)) continue;
1254 
1255  if (filter & ONLY_ENUMERABLE) {
1256  InternalElementsAccessor* accessor =
1257  reinterpret_cast<InternalElementsAccessor*>(
1258  object->GetElementsAccessor());
1259  InternalIndex entry = accessor->GetEntryForIndex(
1260  isolate, *object, object->elements(), index);
1261  if (entry.is_not_found()) continue;
1262  PropertyDetails details = accessor->GetDetails(*object, entry);
1263  if (!details.IsEnumerable()) continue;
1264  }
1265 
1266  DirectHandle<Object> value;
1267  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, index, LookupIterator::OWN);
1268  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, value, Object::GetProperty(&it),
1269  Nothing<bool>());
1270 
1271  if (get_entries) value = MakeEntryPair(isolate, index, value);
1272  values_or_entries->set(count++, *value);
1273  }
1274 
1275  *nof_items = count;
1276  return Just(true);
1277  }
1278 
1279  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT ExceptionStatus CollectElementIndices(
1280  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
1281  KeyAccumulator* keys) final {
1282  return Subclass::CollectElementIndicesImpl(object, backing_store, keys);
1283  }
1284 
1285  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus CollectElementIndicesImpl(
1286  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
1287  KeyAccumulator* keys) {
1288  DCHECK_NE(DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS, kind());
1289  // Non-dictionary elements can't have all-can-read accessors.
1290  size_t length = Subclass::GetMaxIndex(*object, *backing_store);
1291  PropertyFilter filter = keys->filter();
1292  Isolate* isolate = keys->isolate();
1293  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
1294  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
1295  if (Subclass::HasElementImpl(isolate, *object, i, *backing_store,
1296  filter)) {
1297  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(
1298  keys->AddKey(factory->NewNumberFromSize(i)));
1299  }
1300  }
1301  return ExceptionStatus::kSuccess;
1302  }
1303 
1304  static Handle<FixedArray> DirectCollectElementIndicesImpl(
1305  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1306  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store, GetKeysConversion convert,
1307  PropertyFilter filter, Handle<FixedArray> list, uint32_t* nof_indices,
1308  uint32_t insertion_index = 0) {
1309  size_t length = Subclass::GetMaxIndex(*object, *backing_store);
1310  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
1311  if (Subclass::HasElementImpl(isolate, *object, i, *backing_store,
1312  filter)) {
1313  if (convert == GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString) {
1314  // Avoid trashing the number to string cache with numbers that
1315  // are not likely to be needed.
1316  bool use_cache = i < SmiStringCache::kMaxCapacity;
1317  DirectHandle<String> index_string =
1318  isolate->factory()->SizeToString(i, use_cache);
1319  list->set(insertion_index, *index_string);
1320  } else {
1321  DirectHandle<Object> number =
1322  isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromSize(i);
1323  list->set(insertion_index, *number);
1324  }
1325  insertion_index++;
1326  }
1327  }
1328  *nof_indices = insertion_index;
1329  return list;
1330  }
1331 
1332  MaybeHandle<FixedArray> PrependElementIndices(
1333  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1334  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store, DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys,
1335  GetKeysConversion convert, PropertyFilter filter) final {
1336  return Subclass::PrependElementIndicesImpl(isolate, object, backing_store,
1337  keys, convert, filter);
1338  }
1339 
1340  static MaybeHandle<FixedArray> PrependElementIndicesImpl(
1341  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1342  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store, DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys,
1343  GetKeysConversion convert, PropertyFilter filter) {
1344  uint32_t nof_property_keys = keys->length();
1345  size_t initial_list_length =
1346  Subclass::GetMaxNumberOfEntries(isolate, *object, *backing_store);
1347 
1348  if (initial_list_length > FixedArray::kMaxLength - nof_property_keys) {
1349  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1350  NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength));
1351  }
1352  initial_list_length += nof_property_keys;
1353 
1354  // Collect the element indices into a new list.
1355  DCHECK_LE(initial_list_length, std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
1356  MaybeHandle<FixedArray> raw_array = isolate->factory()->TryNewFixedArray(
1357  static_cast<int>(initial_list_length));
1358  Handle<FixedArray> combined_keys;
1359 
1360  // If we have a holey backing store try to precisely estimate the backing
1361  // store size as a last emergency measure if we cannot allocate the big
1362  // array.
1363  if (!raw_array.ToHandle(&combined_keys)) {
1364  if (IsHoleyOrDictionaryElementsKind(kind())) {
1365  // If we overestimate the result list size we might end up in the
1366  // large-object space which doesn't free memory on shrinking the list.
1367  // Hence we try to estimate the final size for holey backing stores more
1368  // precisely here.
1369  initial_list_length =
1370  Subclass::NumberOfElementsImpl(isolate, *object, *backing_store);
1371  initial_list_length += nof_property_keys;
1372  }
1373  DCHECK_LE(initial_list_length, std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
1374  combined_keys = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1375  static_cast<int>(initial_list_length));
1376  }
1377 
1378  uint32_t nof_indices = 0;
1379  bool needs_sorting = IsDictionaryElementsKind(kind()) ||
1380  IsSloppyArgumentsElementsKind(kind());
1381  combined_keys = Subclass::DirectCollectElementIndicesImpl(
1382  isolate, object, backing_store,
1383  needs_sorting ? GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers : convert, filter,
1384  combined_keys, &nof_indices);
1385 
1386  if (needs_sorting) {
1387  SortIndices(isolate, combined_keys, nof_indices);
1388  // Indices from dictionary elements should only be converted after
1389  // sorting.
1390  if (convert == GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString) {
1391  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < nof_indices; i++) {
1392  DirectHandle<Object> index_string =
1393  isolate->factory()->Uint32ToString(
1394  Object::NumberValue(combined_keys->get(i)));
1395  combined_keys->set(i, *index_string);
1396  }
1397  }
1398  }
1399 
1400  // Copy over the passed-in property keys.
1401  CopyObjectToObjectElements(isolate, *keys, PACKED_ELEMENTS, 0,
1402  *combined_keys, PACKED_ELEMENTS, nof_indices,
1403  nof_property_keys);
1404 
1405  // For holey elements and arguments we might have to shrink the collected
1406  // keys since the estimates might be off.
1407  if (IsHoleyOrDictionaryElementsKind(kind()) ||
1408  IsSloppyArgumentsElementsKind(kind())) {
1409  // Shrink combined_keys to the final size.
1410  int final_size = nof_indices + nof_property_keys;
1411  DCHECK_LE(final_size, combined_keys->length());
1412  return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, combined_keys, final_size);
1413  }
1414 
1415  return combined_keys;
1416  }
1417

1420  AddKeyConversion convert) final {

1422  convert);

1494 
1495  static InternalIndex GetEntryForIndexImpl(
1496  Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder,
1497  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store, size_t index,
1498  PropertyFilter filter) {
1499  DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(kind()) ||
1500  IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(kind()));
1501  size_t length = Subclass::GetMaxIndex(holder, backing_store);
1502  if (IsHoleyElementsKindForRead(kind())) {
1503  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1504  index < length,
1505  index <= static_cast<size_t>(std::numeric_limits<int>::max()));
1506  return index < length &&
1507  !Cast<BackingStore>(backing_store)
1508  ->is_the_hole(isolate, static_cast<int>(index))
1509  ? InternalIndex(index)
1510  : InternalIndex::NotFound();
1511  } else {
1512  return index < length ? InternalIndex(index) : InternalIndex::NotFound();
1513  }
1514  }
1515 
1516  InternalIndex GetEntryForIndex(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder,
1517  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
1518  size_t index) final {
1519  return Subclass::GetEntryForIndexImpl(isolate, holder, backing_store, index,
1520  ALL_PROPERTIES);
1521  }

1552 class DictionaryElementsAccessor
1553  : public ElementsAccessorBase<DictionaryElementsAccessor,
1554  ElementsKindTraits<DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS>> {
1555  public:
1556  static uint32_t GetMaxIndex(Tagged<JSObject> receiver,
1557  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements) {
1558  // We cannot properly estimate this for dictionaries.
1559  UNREACHABLE();
1560  }
1561 
1562  static uint32_t GetMaxNumberOfEntries(Isolate* isolate,
1563  Tagged<JSObject> receiver,
1564  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
1565  return NumberOfElementsImpl(isolate, receiver, backing_store);
1566  }
1567 
1568  static uint32_t NumberOfElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate,
1569  Tagged<JSObject> receiver,
1570  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
1571  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dict = Cast<NumberDictionary>(backing_store);
1572  return dict->NumberOfElements();
1573  }
1574 
1575  static Maybe<bool> SetLengthImpl(Isolate* isolate,
1576  DirectHandle<JSArray> array, uint32_t length,
1577  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
1578  auto dict = Cast<NumberDictionary>(backing_store);
1579  uint32_t old_length = 0;
1580  CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(array->length(), &old_length));
1581  {
1582  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1583  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
1584  if (length < old_length) {
1585  if (dict->requires_slow_elements()) {
1586  // Find last non-deletable element in range of elements to be
1587  // deleted and adjust range accordingly.
1588  for (InternalIndex entry : dict->IterateEntries()) {
1589  Tagged<Object> index = dict->KeyAt(isolate, entry);
1590  if (dict->IsKey(roots, index)) {
1591  uint32_t number =
1592  static_cast<uint32_t>(Object::NumberValue(index));
1593  if (length <= number && number < old_length) {
1594  PropertyDetails details = dict->DetailsAt(entry);
1595  if (!details.IsConfigurable()) length = number + 1;
1596  }
1597  }
1598  }
1599  }
1600 
1601  if (length == 0) {
1602  // Flush the backing store.
1603  array->initialize_elements();
1604  } else {
1605  // Remove elements that should be deleted.
1606  int removed_entries = 0;
1607  for (InternalIndex entry : dict->IterateEntries()) {
1608  Tagged<Object> index = dict->KeyAt(isolate, entry);
1609  if (dict->IsKey(roots, index)) {
1610  uint32_t number =
1611  static_cast<uint32_t>(Object::NumberValue(index));
1612  if (length <= number && number < old_length) {
1613  dict->ClearEntry(entry);
1614  removed_entries++;
1615  }
1616  }
1617  }
1618 
1619  if (removed_entries > 0) {
1620  // Update the number of elements.
1621  dict->ElementsRemoved(removed_entries);
1622  }
1623  }
1624  }
1625  }
1626 
1627  DirectHandle<Number> length_obj =
1628  isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(length);
1629  array->set_length(*length_obj);
1630  return Just(true);
1631  }
1632 
1633  static void CopyElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from,
1634  uint32_t from_start, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to,
1635  ElementsKind from_kind, uint32_t to_start,
1636  int packed_size, int copy_size) {
1637  UNREACHABLE();
1638  }

1640  static void DeleteImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
1641  InternalIndex entry) {
1642  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dict(Cast<NumberDictionary>(obj->elements()),
1643  isolate);
1644  dict = NumberDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, dict, entry);
1645  obj->set_elements(*dict);
1646  }
1647 
1648  static bool HasAccessorsImpl(Tagged<JSObject> holder,
1649  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
1650  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1651  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dict = Cast<NumberDictionary>(backing_store);
1652  if (!dict->requires_slow_elements()) return false;
1653  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(holder);
1654  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
1655  for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
1656  Tagged<Object> key = dict->KeyAt(cage_base, i);
1657  if (!dict->IsKey(roots, key)) continue;
1658  PropertyDetails details = dict->DetailsAt(i);
1659  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor) return true;
1660  }
1661  return false;
1662  }

1714  static void ReconfigureImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1715  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> store,
1716  InternalIndex entry, DirectHandle<Object> value,
1717  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
1718  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary = Cast<NumberDictionary>(*store);
1719  if (attributes != NONE) object->RequireSlowElements(dictionary);
1720  dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
1721  PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(entry);
1722  details =
1723  PropertyDetails(PropertyKind::kData, attributes,
1724  PropertyCellType::kNoCell, details.dictionary_index());
1725 
1726  dictionary->DetailsAtPut(entry, details);
1727  }

1729  static Maybe<bool> AddImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1730  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
1731  PropertyAttributes attributes,
1732  uint32_t new_capacity) {
1733  PropertyDetails details(PropertyKind::kData, attributes,
1734  PropertyCellType::kNoCell);
1735  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
1736  object->HasFastElements() || object->HasFastStringWrapperElements()
1737  ? JSObject::NormalizeElements(isolate, object)
1738  : direct_handle(Cast<NumberDictionary>(object->elements()),
1739  isolate);
1740  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> new_dictionary =
1741  NumberDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, index, value, details);
1742  new_dictionary->UpdateMaxNumberKey(index, object);
1743  if (attributes != NONE) object->RequireSlowElements(*new_dictionary);
1744  if (dictionary.is_identical_to(new_dictionary)) return Just(true);
1745  object->set_elements(*new_dictionary);
1746  return Just(true);
1747  }

1749  static bool HasEntryImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> store,
1750  InternalIndex entry) {
1751  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1752  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dict = Cast<NumberDictionary>(store);
1753  Tagged<Object> index = dict->KeyAt(isolate, entry);
1754  return !IsTheHole(index, isolate);
1755  }

1757  static InternalIndex GetEntryForIndexImpl(Isolate* isolate,
1758  Tagged<JSObject> holder,
1759  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> store,
1760  size_t index,
1761  PropertyFilter filter) {
1762  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1763  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary = Cast<NumberDictionary>(store);
1764  DCHECK_LE(index, std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
1765  InternalIndex entry =
1766  dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
1767  if (entry.is_not_found()) return entry;
1768 
1769  if (filter != ALL_PROPERTIES) {
1770  PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(entry);
1771  PropertyAttributes attr = details.attributes();
1772  if ((int{attr} & filter) != 0) return InternalIndex::NotFound();
1773  }
1774  return entry;
1775  }

1786 
1787  static uint32_t FilterKey(DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary,
1788  InternalIndex entry, Tagged<Object> raw_key,
1789  PropertyFilter filter) {
1790  DCHECK(IsNumber(raw_key));
1791  DCHECK_LE(Object::NumberValue(raw_key), kMaxUInt32);
1792  PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(entry);
1793  PropertyAttributes attr = details.attributes();
1794  if ((int{attr} & filter) != 0) return kMaxUInt32;
1795  return static_cast<uint32_t>(Object::NumberValue(raw_key));
1796  }
1797 
1798  static uint32_t GetKeyForEntryImpl(Isolate* isolate,
1799  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary,
1800  InternalIndex entry,
1801  PropertyFilter filter) {
1802  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1803  Tagged<Object> raw_key = dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry);
1804  if (!dictionary->IsKey(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), raw_key)) return kMaxUInt32;
1805  return FilterKey(dictionary, entry, raw_key, filter);
1806  }
1807 
1808  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus CollectElementIndicesImpl(
1809  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
1810  KeyAccumulator* keys) {
1811  if (keys->filter() & SKIP_STRINGS) return ExceptionStatus::kSuccess;
1812  Isolate* isolate = keys->isolate();
1813  auto dictionary = Cast<NumberDictionary>(backing_store);
1814  DirectHandle<FixedArray> elements = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1815  GetMaxNumberOfEntries(isolate, *object, *backing_store));
1816  int insertion_index = 0;
1817  PropertyFilter filter = keys->filter();
1818  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
1819  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
1820  AllowGarbageCollection allow_gc;
1821  Tagged<Object> raw_key = dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, i);
1822  if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, raw_key)) continue;
1823  uint32_t key = FilterKey(dictionary, i, raw_key, filter);
1824  if (key == kMaxUInt32) {
1825  // This might allocate, but {raw_key} is not used afterwards.
1826  keys->AddShadowingKey(raw_key, &allow_gc);
1827  continue;
1828  }
1829  elements->set(insertion_index, raw_key);
1830  insertion_index++;
1831  }
1832  SortIndices(isolate, elements, insertion_index);
1833  for (int i = 0; i < insertion_index; i++) {
1834  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(keys->AddKey(elements->get(i)));
1835  }
1836  return ExceptionStatus::kSuccess;
1837  }
1838 
1839  static Handle<FixedArray> DirectCollectElementIndicesImpl(
1840  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
1841  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store, GetKeysConversion convert,
1842  PropertyFilter filter, Handle<FixedArray> list, uint32_t* nof_indices,
1843  uint32_t insertion_index = 0) {
1844  if (filter & SKIP_STRINGS) return list;
1845 
1846  auto dictionary = Cast<NumberDictionary>(backing_store);
1847  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
1848  uint32_t key = GetKeyForEntryImpl(isolate, dictionary, i, filter);
1849  if (key == kMaxUInt32) continue;
1850  DirectHandle<Object> index = isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(key);
1851  list->set(insertion_index, *index);
1852  insertion_index++;
1853  }
1854  *nof_indices = insertion_index;
1855  return list;
1856  }
1857 
1858  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus AddElementsToKeyAccumulatorImpl(
1859  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver, KeyAccumulator* accumulator,
1860  AddKeyConversion convert) {
1861  Isolate* isolate = accumulator->isolate();
1862  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary(
1863  Cast<NumberDictionary>(receiver->elements()), isolate);
1864  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
1865  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
1866  Tagged<Object> k = dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, i);
1867  if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, k)) continue;
1868  Tagged<Object> value = dictionary->ValueAt(isolate, i);
1869  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(value, isolate));
1870  DCHECK(!IsAccessorPair(value));
1871  DCHECK(!IsAccessorInfo(value));
1872  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(accumulator->AddKey(value, convert));
1873  }
1874  return ExceptionStatus::kSuccess;
1875  }
1876 
1877  static bool IncludesValueFastPath(Isolate* isolate,
1878  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
1879  DirectHandle<Object> value,
1880  size_t start_from, size_t length,
1881  Maybe<bool>* result) {
1882  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1883  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
1884  Cast<NumberDictionary>(receiver->elements());
1885  Tagged<Object> the_hole = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).the_hole_value();
1886  Tagged<Object> undefined = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value();
1887 
1888  // Scan for accessor properties. If accessors are present, then elements
1889  // must be accessed in order via the slow path.
1890  bool found = false;
1891  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
1892  Tagged<Object> k = dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, i);
1893  if (k == the_hole) continue;
1894  if (k == undefined) continue;
1895 
1896  uint32_t index;
1897  if (!Object::ToArrayIndex(k, &index) || index < start_from ||
1898  index >= length) {
1899  continue;
1900  }
1901 
1902  if (dictionary->DetailsAt(i).kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor) {
1903  // Restart from beginning in slow path, otherwise we may observably
1904  // access getters out of order
1905  return false;
1906  } else if (!found) {
1907  Tagged<Object> element_k = dictionary->ValueAt(isolate, i);
1908  if (Object::SameValueZero(*value, element_k)) found = true;
1909  }
1910  }
1911 
1912  *result = Just(found);
1913  return true;
1914  }
1915 
1916  static Maybe<bool> IncludesValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
1917  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
1918  DirectHandle<Object> value,
1919  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
1920  DCHECK(JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *receiver));
1921  bool search_for_hole = IsUndefined(*value, isolate);
1922 
1923  if (!search_for_hole) {
1924  Maybe<bool> result = Nothing<bool>();
1925  if (DictionaryElementsAccessor::IncludesValueFastPath(
1926  isolate, receiver, value, start_from, length, &result)) {
1927  return result;
1928  }
1929  }
1930  ElementsKind original_elements_kind = receiver->GetElementsKind();
1931  USE(original_elements_kind);
1932  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary(
1933  Cast<NumberDictionary>(receiver->elements()), isolate);
1934  // Iterate through the entire range, as accessing elements out of order is
1935  // observable.
1936  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
1937  DCHECK_EQ(receiver->GetElementsKind(), original_elements_kind);
1938  InternalIndex entry =
1939  dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, static_cast<uint32_t>(k));
1940  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
1941  if (search_for_hole) return Just(true);
1942  continue;
1943  }
1944 
1945  PropertyDetails details = GetDetailsImpl(*dictionary, entry);
1946  switch (details.kind()) {
1947  case PropertyKind::kData: {
1948  Tagged<Object> element_k = dictionary->ValueAt(entry);
1949  if (Object::SameValueZero(*value, element_k)) return Just(true);
1950  break;
1951  }
1952  case PropertyKind::kAccessor: {
1953  LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, k,
1954  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
1955  DCHECK(it.IsFound());
1956  DCHECK_EQ(it.state(), LookupIterator::ACCESSOR);
1957  DirectHandle<Object> element_k;
1958 
1959  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, element_k,
1960  Object::GetPropertyWithAccessor(&it),
1961  Nothing<bool>());
1962 
1963  if (Object::SameValueZero(*value, *element_k)) return Just(true);
1964 
1965  // Bailout to slow path if elements on prototype changed
1966  if (!JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *receiver)) {
1967  return IncludesValueSlowPath(isolate, receiver, value, k + 1,
1968  length);
1969  }
1970 
1971  // Continue if elements unchanged
1972  if (*dictionary == receiver->elements()) continue;
1973 
1974  // Otherwise, bailout or update elements
1975 
1976  // If switched to initial elements, return true if searching for
1977  // undefined, and false otherwise.
1978  if (receiver->map()->GetInitialElements() == receiver->elements()) {
1979  return Just(search_for_hole);
1980  }
1981 
1982  // If switched to fast elements, continue with the correct accessor.
1983  if (receiver->GetElementsKind() != DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS) {
1984  ElementsAccessor* accessor = receiver->GetElementsAccessor();
1985  return accessor->IncludesValue(isolate, receiver, value, k + 1,
1986  length);
1987  }
1988  dictionary = direct_handle(
1989  Cast<NumberDictionary>(receiver->elements()), isolate);
1990  break;
1991  }
1992  }
1993  }
1994  return Just(false);
1995  }
1996 
1997  static Maybe<int64_t> IndexOfValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
1998  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
1999  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2000  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
2001  DCHECK(JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *receiver));
2002 
2003  ElementsKind original_elements_kind = receiver->GetElementsKind();
2004  USE(original_elements_kind);
2005  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary(
2006  Cast<NumberDictionary>(receiver->elements()), isolate);
2007  // Iterate through entire range, as accessing elements out of order is
2008  // observable.
2009  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2010  DCHECK_EQ(receiver->GetElementsKind(), original_elements_kind);
2011  DCHECK_LE(k, std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
2012  InternalIndex entry =
2013  dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, static_cast<uint32_t>(k));
2014  if (entry.is_not_found()) continue;
2015 
2016  PropertyDetails details =
2017  GetDetailsImpl(*dictionary, InternalIndex(entry));
2018  switch (details.kind()) {
2019  case PropertyKind::kData: {
2020  Tagged<Object> element_k = dictionary->ValueAt(entry);
2021  if (Object::StrictEquals(*value, element_k)) {
2022  return Just<int64_t>(k);
2023  }
2024  break;
2025  }
2026  case PropertyKind::kAccessor: {
2027  LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, k,
2028  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
2029  DCHECK(it.IsFound());
2030  DCHECK_EQ(it.state(), LookupIterator::ACCESSOR);
2031  DirectHandle<Object> element_k;
2032 
2033  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, element_k,
2034  Object::GetPropertyWithAccessor(&it),
2035  Nothing<int64_t>());
2036 
2037  if (Object::StrictEquals(*value, *element_k)) return Just<int64_t>(k);
2038 
2039  // Bailout to slow path if elements on prototype changed.
2040  if (!JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *receiver)) {
2041  return IndexOfValueSlowPath(isolate, receiver, value, k + 1,
2042  length);
2043  }
2044 
2045  // Continue if elements unchanged.
2046  if (*dictionary == receiver->elements()) continue;
2047 
2048  // Otherwise, bailout or update elements.
2049  if (receiver->GetElementsKind() != DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS) {
2050  // Otherwise, switch to slow path.
2051  return IndexOfValueSlowPath(isolate, receiver, value, k + 1,
2052  length);
2053  }
2054  dictionary = direct_handle(
2055  Cast<NumberDictionary>(receiver->elements()), isolate);
2056  break;
2057  }
2058  }
2059  }
2060  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
2061  }
2062 
2063  static void ValidateContents(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder,
2064  size_t length) {
2065  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2066 #if DEBUG
2067  DCHECK_EQ(holder->map()->elements_kind(), DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS);
2068  if (!v8_flags.enable_slow_asserts) return;
2069  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
2070  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
2071  Cast<NumberDictionary>(holder->elements());
2072  // Validate the requires_slow_elements and max_number_key values.
2073  bool requires_slow_elements = false;
2074  int max_key = 0;
2075  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
2076  Tagged<Object> k;
2077  if (!dictionary->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
2078  DCHECK_LE(0.0, Object::NumberValue(k));
2079  if (Object::NumberValue(k) >
2080  NumberDictionary::kRequiresSlowElementsLimit) {
2081  requires_slow_elements = true;
2082  } else {
2083  max_key = std::max(max_key, Smi::ToInt(k));
2084  }
2085  }
2086  if (requires_slow_elements) {
2087  DCHECK(dictionary->requires_slow_elements());
2088  } else if (!dictionary->requires_slow_elements()) {
2089  DCHECK_LE(max_key, dictionary->max_number_key());
2090  }
2091 #endif
2092  }
2093 };
2094 
2095 // Super class for all fast element arrays.
2096 template <typename Subclass, typename KindTraits>
2097 class FastElementsAccessor : public ElementsAccessorBase<Subclass, KindTraits> {
2098  public:
2099  using BackingStore = typename KindTraits::BackingStore;
2100 
2101  static DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> NormalizeImpl(
2102  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
2103  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> store) {
2104  ElementsKind kind = Subclass::kind();
2105 
2106  // Ensure that notifications fire if the array or object prototypes are
2107  // normalizing.
2108  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind) ||
2109  kind == FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS) {
2110  isolate->UpdateNoElementsProtectorOnNormalizeElements(object);
2111  }
2112 
2113  int capacity = object->GetFastElementsUsage();
2114  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
2115  NumberDictionary::New(isolate, capacity);
2116 
2117  PropertyDetails details = PropertyDetails::Empty();
2118  int j = 0;
2119  int max_number_key = -1;
2120  for (int i = 0; j < capacity; i++) {
2121  if (IsHoleyElementsKindForRead(kind)) {
2122  if (Cast<BackingStore>(*store)->is_the_hole(isolate, i)) continue;
2123  }
2124  max_number_key = i;
2125  DirectHandle<Object> value =
2126  Subclass::GetImpl(isolate, *store, InternalIndex(i));
2127  dictionary =
2128  NumberDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, i, value, details);
2129  j++;
2130  }
2131 
2132  if (max_number_key > 0) {
2133  dictionary->UpdateMaxNumberKey(static_cast<uint32_t>(max_number_key),
2134  object);
2135  }
2136  return dictionary;
2137  }
2138 
2139  static void DeleteAtEnd(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
2140  DirectHandle<BackingStore> backing_store,
2141  uint32_t entry) {
2142  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(backing_store->length());
2143  DCHECK_LT(entry, length);
2144  for (; entry > 0; entry--) {
2145  if (!backing_store->is_the_hole(isolate, entry - 1)) break;
2146  }
2147  if (entry == 0) {
2148  Tagged<FixedArray> empty = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array();
2149  // Dynamically ask for the elements kind here since we manually redirect
2150  // the operations for argument backing stores.
2151  if (obj->GetElementsKind() == FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS) {
2152  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(obj->elements())->set_arguments(empty);
2153  } else {
2154  obj->set_elements(empty);
2155  }
2156  return;
2157  }
2158 
2159  isolate->heap()->RightTrimArray(*backing_store, entry, length);
2160  }
2161 
2162  static void DeleteCommon(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
2163  uint32_t entry, DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> store) {
2164  DCHECK(obj->HasSmiOrObjectElements() || obj->HasDoubleElements() ||
2165  obj->HasNonextensibleElements() || obj->HasFastArgumentsElements() ||
2166  obj->HasFastStringWrapperElements());
2167  DirectHandle<BackingStore> backing_store = Cast<BackingStore>(store);
2168  if (!IsJSArray(*obj) &&
2169  entry == static_cast<uint32_t>(store->length()) - 1) {
2170  DeleteAtEnd(isolate, obj, backing_store, entry);
2171  return;
2172  }
2173 
2174  backing_store->set_the_hole(isolate, entry);
2175 
2176  // TODO(verwaest): Move this out of elements.cc.
2177  // If the backing store is larger than a certain size and
2178  // has too few used values, normalize it.
2179  const int kMinLengthForSparsenessCheck = 64;
2180  if (backing_store->length() < kMinLengthForSparsenessCheck) return;
2181  uint32_t length = 0;
2182  if (IsJSArray(*obj)) {
2183  Object::ToArrayLength(Cast<JSArray>(*obj)->length(), &length);
2184  } else {
2185  length = static_cast<uint32_t>(store->length());
2186  }
2187 
2188  // To avoid doing the check on every delete, use a counter-based heuristic.
2189  const int kLengthFraction = 16;
2190  // The above constant must be large enough to ensure that we check for
2191  // normalization frequently enough. At a minimum, it should be large
2192  // enough to reliably hit the "window" of remaining elements count where
2193  // normalization would be beneficial.
2194  static_assert(kLengthFraction >=
2195  NumberDictionary::kEntrySize *
2196  NumberDictionary::kPreferFastElementsSizeFactor);
2197  size_t current_counter = isolate->elements_deletion_counter();
2198  if (current_counter < length / kLengthFraction) {
2199  isolate->set_elements_deletion_counter(current_counter + 1);
2200  return;
2201  }
2202  // Reset the counter whenever the full check is performed.
2203  isolate->set_elements_deletion_counter(0);
2204 
2205  if (!IsJSArray(*obj)) {
2206  uint32_t i;
2207  for (i = entry + 1; i < length; i++) {
2208  if (!backing_store->is_the_hole(isolate, i)) break;
2209  }
2210  if (i == length) {
2211  DeleteAtEnd(isolate, obj, backing_store, entry);
2212  return;
2213  }
2214  }
2215  int num_used = 0;
2216  for (int i = 0; i < backing_store->length(); ++i) {
2217  if (!backing_store->is_the_hole(isolate, i)) {
2218  ++num_used;
2219  // Bail out if a number dictionary wouldn't be able to save much space.
2220  if (NumberDictionary::kPreferFastElementsSizeFactor *
2221  NumberDictionary::ComputeCapacity(num_used) *
2222  NumberDictionary::kEntrySize >
2223  static_cast<uint32_t>(backing_store->length())) {
2224  return;
2225  }
2226  }
2227  }
2228  JSObject::NormalizeElements(isolate, obj);
2229  }
2230 
2231  static void ReconfigureImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
2232  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> store,
2233  InternalIndex entry, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2234  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
2235  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
2236  JSObject::NormalizeElements(isolate, object);
2237  entry = InternalIndex(dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, entry.as_uint32()));
2238  DictionaryElementsAccessor::ReconfigureImpl(
2239  isolate, object, Cast<FixedArrayBase>(dictionary), entry, value,
2240  attributes);
2241  }
2242 
2243  static Maybe<bool> AddImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
2244  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2245  PropertyAttributes attributes,
2246  uint32_t new_capacity) {
2247  DCHECK_EQ(NONE, attributes);
2248  ElementsKind from_kind = object->GetElementsKind();
2249  ElementsKind to_kind = Subclass::kind();
2250  if (IsDictionaryElementsKind(from_kind) ||
2251  IsDoubleElementsKind(from_kind) != IsDoubleElementsKind(to_kind) ||
2252  Subclass::GetCapacityImpl(*object, object->elements()) !=
2253  new_capacity) {
2254  MAYBE_RETURN(
2255  Subclass::GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(isolate, object, new_capacity),
2256  Nothing<bool>());
2257  } else {
2258  if (IsFastElementsKind(from_kind) && from_kind != to_kind) {
2259  JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(isolate, object, to_kind);
2260  }
2261  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(from_kind)) {
2262  DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(to_kind));
2263  JSObject::EnsureWritableFastElements(isolate, object);
2264  }
2265  }
2266  Subclass::SetImpl(object, InternalIndex(index), *value);
2267  return Just(true);
2268  }
2269 
2270  static void DeleteImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
2271  InternalIndex entry) {
2272  ElementsKind kind = KindTraits::Kind;
2273  if (IsFastPackedElementsKind(kind) ||
2274  kind == PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS) {
2275  JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(isolate, obj,
2276  GetHoleyElementsKind(kind));
2277  }
2278  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind) ||
2279  IsNonextensibleElementsKind(kind)) {
2280  JSObject::EnsureWritableFastElements(isolate, obj);
2281  }
2282  DeleteCommon(isolate, obj, entry.as_uint32(),
2283  direct_handle(obj->elements(), isolate));
2284  }
2285 
2286  static bool HasEntryImpl(Isolate* isolate,
2287  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
2288  InternalIndex entry) {
2289  return !Cast<BackingStore>(backing_store)
2290  ->is_the_hole(isolate, entry.as_int());
2291  }
2292 
2293  static uint32_t NumberOfElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate,
2294  Tagged<JSObject> receiver,
2295  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
2296  size_t max_index = Subclass::GetMaxIndex(receiver, backing_store);
2297  DCHECK_LE(max_index, std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
2298  if (IsFastPackedElementsKind(Subclass::kind())) {
2299  return static_cast<uint32_t>(max_index);
2300  }
2301  uint32_t count = 0;
2302  for (size_t i = 0; i < max_index; i++) {
2303  if (Subclass::HasEntryImpl(isolate, backing_store, InternalIndex(i))) {
2304  count++;
2305  }
2306  }
2307  return count;
2308  }

2310  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus AddElementsToKeyAccumulatorImpl(
2311  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver, KeyAccumulator* accumulator,
2312  AddKeyConversion convert) {
2313  Isolate* isolate = accumulator->isolate();
2314  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements(receiver->elements(), isolate);
2315  size_t length =
2316  Subclass::GetMaxNumberOfEntries(isolate, *receiver, *elements);
2317  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2318  if (IsFastPackedElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind) ||
2319  HasEntryImpl(isolate, *elements, InternalIndex(i))) {
2320  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(accumulator->AddKey(
2321  Subclass::GetImpl(isolate, *elements, InternalIndex(i)), convert));
2322  }
2323  }
2324  return ExceptionStatus::kSuccess;
2325  }
2326 
2327  static void ValidateContents(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder,
2328  size_t length) {
2329 #if DEBUG
2330  Heap* heap = isolate->heap();
2331  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements = holder->elements();
2332  Tagged<Map> map = elements->map();
2333  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind)) {
2334  DCHECK_NE(map, ReadOnlyRoots(heap).fixed_double_array_map());
2335  } else if (IsDoubleElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind)) {
2336  DCHECK_NE(map, ReadOnlyRoots(heap).fixed_cow_array_map());
2337  if (map == ReadOnlyRoots(heap).fixed_array_map()) DCHECK_EQ(0u, length);
2338  } else {
2339  UNREACHABLE();
2340  }
2341  if (length == 0u) return; // nothing to do!
2342 #if ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
2343  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2344  Tagged<BackingStore> backing_store = Cast<BackingStore>(elements);
2345  DCHECK(length <= std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
2346  int length_int = static_cast<int>(length);
2347  int capacity_int = static_cast<int>(backing_store->length());
2348  if (IsSmiElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind)) {
2349  HandleScope scope(isolate);
2350  for (int i = 0; i < length_int; i++) {
2351  Tagged<Object> element = Cast<FixedArray>(backing_store)->get(i);
2352  DCHECK(IsSmi(element) || (IsHoleyElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind) &&
2353  IsTheHole(element, isolate)));
2354  }
2355  } else if (KindTraits::Kind == PACKED_ELEMENTS ||
2356  KindTraits::Kind == PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
2357  for (int i = 0; i < length_int; i++) {
2358  DCHECK(!backing_store->is_the_hole(isolate, i));
2359  }
2360  } else {
2361  DCHECK(IsHoleyElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind));
2362  }
2363  // Any values in the backing store outside of the length have to be holes,
2364  // even if it is PACKED, in case it is extended (and made HOLEY as part of
2365  // that extension).
2366  for (int i = length_int; i < capacity_int; i++) {
2367  DCHECK(backing_store->is_the_hole(isolate, i));
2368  }
2369 #endif
2370 #endif
2371  }

2378  static Tagged<Object> ShiftImpl(Isolate* isolate,
2379  DirectHandle<JSArray> receiver) {
