2400  static MaybeDirectHandle<Object> FillImpl(Isolate* isolate,
2401  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
2402  DirectHandle<Object> obj_value,
2403  size_t start, size_t end) {
2404  // Ensure indexes are within array bounds
2405  DCHECK_LE(0, start);
2406  DCHECK_LE(start, end);
2407 
2408  // Make sure COW arrays are copied.
2409  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(Subclass::kind())) {
2410  JSObject::EnsureWritableFastElements(isolate, receiver);
2411  }
2412 
2413  // Make sure we have enough space.
2414  DCHECK_LE(end, std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
2415  if (end > Subclass::GetCapacityImpl(*receiver, receiver->elements())) {
2416  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(Subclass::GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(
2417  isolate, receiver, static_cast<uint32_t>(end)));
2418  CHECK_EQ(Subclass::kind(), receiver->GetElementsKind());
2419  }
2420  DCHECK_LE(end, Subclass::GetCapacityImpl(*receiver, receiver->elements()));
2421 
2422  for (size_t index = start; index < end; ++index) {
2423  Subclass::SetImpl(receiver, InternalIndex(index), *obj_value);
2424  }
2425  return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>(receiver);
2426  }
2427 
2428  static Maybe<bool> IncludesValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
2429  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
2430  DirectHandle<Object> search_value,
2431  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
2432  DCHECK(JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *receiver));
2433  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2434  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements_base = receiver->elements();
2435  Tagged<Object> the_hole = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).the_hole_value();
2436  Tagged<Object> undefined = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value();
2437  Tagged<Object> value = *search_value;
2438 
2439  if (start_from >= length) return Just(false);
2440 
2441  // Elements beyond the capacity of the backing store treated as undefined.
2442  size_t elements_length = static_cast<size_t>(elements_base->length());
2443  if (value == undefined && elements_length < length) return Just(true);
2444  if (elements_length == 0) {
2445  DCHECK_NE(value, undefined);
2446  return Just(false);
2447  }
2448 
2449  length = std::min(elements_length, length);
2450  DCHECK_LE(length, std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
2451 
2452  if (!IsNumber(value)) {
2453  if (value == undefined) {
2454  // Search for `undefined` or The Hole. Even in the case of
2455  // PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS or PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS, we might encounter The
2456  // Hole here, since the {length} used here can be larger than
2457  // JSArray::length.
2458  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(Subclass::kind()) ||
2459  IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(Subclass::kind())) {
2460  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(receiver->elements());
2461 
2462  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2463  Tagged<Object> element_k = elements->get(static_cast<int>(k));
2464 
2465  if (element_k == the_hole || element_k == undefined) {
2466  return Just(true);
2467  }
2468  }
2469  return Just(false);
2470  } else {
2471  // Search for The Hole in HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS or
2472  // PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
2473  DCHECK(IsDoubleElementsKind(Subclass::kind()));
2474  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> elements =
2475  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(receiver->elements());
2476 
2477  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2478  if (elements->is_the_hole(static_cast<int>(k))) return Just(true);
2479  }
2480  return Just(false);
2481  }
2482  } else if (!IsObjectElementsKind(Subclass::kind()) &&
2483  !IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(Subclass::kind())) {
2484  // Search for non-number, non-Undefined value, with either
2485  // PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS, PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or
2486  // HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS. Guaranteed to return false, since these
2487  // elements kinds can only contain Number values or undefined.
2488  return Just(false);
2489  } else {
2490  // Search for non-number, non-Undefined value with either
2491  // PACKED_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2492  DCHECK(IsObjectElementsKind(Subclass::kind()) ||
2493  IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(Subclass::kind()));
2494  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(receiver->elements());
2495 
2496  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2497  Tagged<Object> element_k = elements->get(static_cast<int>(k));
2498  if (element_k == the_hole) continue;
2499  if (Object::SameValueZero(value, element_k)) return Just(true);
2500  }
2501  return Just(false);
2502  }
2503  } else {
2504  if (!IsNaN(value)) {
2505  double search_number = Object::NumberValue(value);
2506  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(Subclass::kind())) {
2507  // Search for non-NaN Number in PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS or
2508  // HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS --- Skip TheHole, and trust UCOMISD or
2509  // similar operation for result.
2510  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> elements =
2511  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(receiver->elements());
2512 
2513  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2514  if (elements->is_the_hole(static_cast<int>(k))) continue;
2515  if (elements->get_scalar(static_cast<int>(k)) == search_number) {
2516  return Just(true);
2517  }
2518  }
2519  return Just(false);
2520  } else {
2521  // Search for non-NaN Number in PACKED_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2522  // PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS --- Skip non-Numbers,
2523  // and trust UCOMISD or similar operation for result
2524  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(receiver->elements());
2525 
2526  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2527  Tagged<Object> element_k = elements->get(static_cast<int>(k));
2528  if (IsNumber(element_k) &&
2529  Object::NumberValue(element_k) == search_number) {
2530  return Just(true);
2531  }
2532  }
2533  return Just(false);
2534  }
2535  } else {
2536  // Search for NaN --- NaN cannot be represented with Smi elements, so
2537  // abort if ElementsKind is PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS
2538  if (IsSmiElementsKind(Subclass::kind())) return Just(false);
2539 
2540  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(Subclass::kind())) {
2541  // Search for NaN in PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS or
2542  // HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS --- Skip The Hole and trust
2543  // std::isnan(elementK) for result
2544  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> elements =
2545  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(receiver->elements());
2546 
2547  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2548  if (elements->is_the_hole(static_cast<int>(k))) continue;
2549  if (std::isnan(elements->get_scalar(static_cast<int>(k)))) {
2550  return Just(true);
2551  }
2552  }
2553  return Just(false);
2554  } else {
2555  // Search for NaN in PACKED_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS. Return true
2556  // if elementK->IsHeapNumber() && std::isnan(elementK->Number())
2557  DCHECK(IsObjectElementsKind(Subclass::kind()) ||
2558  IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(Subclass::kind()));
2559  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(receiver->elements());
2560 
2561  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2562  if (IsNaN(elements->get(static_cast<int>(k)))) return Just(true);
2563  }
2564  return Just(false);
2565  }
2566  }
2567  }
2568  }
2569 
2570  static Handle<FixedArray> CreateListFromArrayLikeImpl(
2571  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, uint32_t length) {
2572  Handle<FixedArray> result = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(length);
2573  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements(object->elements(), isolate);
2574  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2575  InternalIndex entry(i);
2576  if (!Subclass::HasEntryImpl(isolate, *elements, entry)) continue;
2577  DirectHandle<Object> value;
2578  value = Subclass::GetImpl(isolate, *elements, entry);
2579  if (IsName(*value)) {
2580  value = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(Cast<Name>(value));
2581  }
2582  result->set(i, *value);
2583  }
2584  return result;
2585  }
2586 
2587  static V8_INLINE Tagged<Object> RemoveElement(Isolate* isolate,
2588  DirectHandle<JSArray> receiver,
2589  Where remove_position) {
2590  constexpr ElementsKind kind = KindTraits::Kind;
2591  static_assert(IsFastElementsKind(kind));
2592  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::ToInt(receiver->length()));
2593  if (length == 0) return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value();
2594 
2595  if constexpr (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) {
2596  JSObject::EnsureWritableFastElements(isolate, receiver);
2597  }
2598 
2599  DCHECK_GT(length, 0);
2600  int new_length = length - 1;
2601  int remove_index = remove_position == AT_START ? 0 : new_length;
2602  Tagged<Object> result;
2603  Tagged<JSArray> raw_receiver = *receiver;
2604  if constexpr (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
2605  result = *Subclass::GetImpl(isolate, raw_receiver->elements(),
2606  InternalIndex(remove_index));
2607  raw_receiver = *receiver;
2608  } else {
2609  result = Cast<BackingStore>(raw_receiver->elements())->get(remove_index);
2610  }
2611  // The result is now unhandlified, so we can't allocate anymore.
2612  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2613  if (V8_UNLIKELY(new_length == 0)) {
2614  raw_receiver->initialize_elements();
2615  } else {
2616  Tagged<BackingStore> dst_elms =
2617  Cast<BackingStore>(raw_receiver->elements());
2618  if (remove_position == AT_START) {
2619  if (V8_UNLIKELY(new_length > JSArray::kMaxCopyElements &&
2620  isolate->heap()->CanMoveObjectStart(dst_elms))) {
2621  dst_elms = Cast<BackingStore>(
2622  isolate->heap()->LeftTrimFixedArray(dst_elms, 1));
2623  raw_receiver->set_elements(dst_elms);
2624  } else {
2625  WriteBarrierMode mode = IsFastNumberElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind)
2626  ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER
2627  : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
2628  dst_elms->MoveElements(isolate, 0, 1, new_length, mode);
2629  dst_elms->FillWithHoles(new_length, new_length + 1);
2630  Subclass::DecreaseLength(isolate, dst_elms, length, new_length);
2631  }
2632  } else {
2633  dst_elms->FillWithHoles(new_length, new_length + 1);
2634  Subclass::DecreaseLength(isolate, dst_elms, length, new_length);
2635  }
2636  }
2637  raw_receiver->set_length(Smi::FromInt(new_length));
2638 
2639  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind) && IsTheHole(result, isolate)) {
2640  return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value();
2641  }
2642  return result;
2643  }
2644 
2645  static Maybe<uint32_t> AddArguments(
2646  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSArray> receiver,
2647  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store, BuiltinArguments* args,
2648  uint32_t add_size, Where add_position) {
2649  uint32_t length = Smi::ToInt(receiver->length());
2650  DCHECK_LT(0, add_size);
2651  uint32_t elms_len = backing_store->length();
2652  // Check we do not overflow the new_length.
2653  DCHECK(add_size <= static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::kMaxValue - length));
2654  uint32_t new_length = length + add_size;
2655 
2656  if (new_length > elms_len) {
2657  // New backing storage is needed.
2658  uint32_t capacity = JSObject::NewElementsCapacity(new_length);
2659  // If we add arguments to the start we have to shift the existing objects.
2660  int copy_dst_index = add_position == AT_START ? add_size : 0;
2661  // Copy over all objects to a new backing_store.
2662  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2663  isolate, backing_store,
2664  Subclass::ConvertElementsWithCapacity(isolate, receiver,
2665  backing_store, KindTraits::Kind,
2666  capacity, 0, copy_dst_index),
2667  Nothing<uint32_t>());
2668  receiver->set_elements(*backing_store);
2669  } else if (add_position == AT_START) {
2670  // If the backing store has enough capacity and we add elements to the
2671  // start we have to shift the existing objects.
2672  WriteBarrierMode mode = IsFastNumberElementsKind(KindTraits::Kind)
2673  ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER
2674  : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
2675  Cast<BackingStore>(backing_store)
2676  ->MoveElements(isolate, add_size, 0, length, mode);
2677  }
2678 
2679  int insertion_index = add_position == AT_START ? 0 : length;
2680  // Copy the arguments to the start.
2681  Subclass::CopyArguments(args, backing_store, add_size, 1, insertion_index);
2682  // Set the length.
2683  receiver->set_length(Smi::FromInt(new_length));
2684  return Just(new_length);
2685  }
2686 
2687  static void CopyArguments(BuiltinArguments* args,
2688  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> dst_store,
2689  uint32_t copy_size, uint32_t src_index,
2690  uint32_t dst_index) {
2691  // Add the provided values.
2692  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2693  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> raw_backing_store = *dst_store;
2694  WriteBarrierMode mode = raw_backing_store->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
2695  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < copy_size; i++) {
2696  Tagged<Object> argument = (*args)[src_index + i];
2697  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(argument));
2698  Subclass::SetImpl(raw_backing_store, InternalIndex(dst_index + i),
2699  argument, mode);
2700  }
2701  }
2702 };
2703 
2704 template <typename Subclass, typename KindTraits>
2705 class FastSmiOrObjectElementsAccessor
2706  : public FastElementsAccessor<Subclass, KindTraits> {
2707  public:
2708  static inline void SetImpl(DirectHandle<JSObject> holder, InternalIndex entry,
2709  Tagged<Object> value) {
2710  SetImpl(holder->elements(), entry, value);
2711  }
2712 
2713  static inline void SetImpl(Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
2714  InternalIndex entry, Tagged<Object> value) {
2715  Cast<FixedArray>(backing_store)->set(entry.as_int(), value);
2716  }
2717 
2718  static inline void SetImpl(Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
2719  InternalIndex entry, Tagged<Object> value,
2720  WriteBarrierMode mode) {
2721  Cast<FixedArray>(backing_store)->set(entry.as_int(), value, mode);
2722  }
2723 
2724  static Tagged<Object> GetRaw(Tagged<FixedArray> backing_store,
2725  InternalIndex entry) {
2726  return backing_store->get(entry.as_int());
2727  }
2728 
2729  // NOTE: this method violates the handlified function signature convention:
2730  // raw pointer parameters in the function that allocates.
2731  // See ElementsAccessor::CopyElements() for details.
2732  // This method could actually allocate if copying from double elements to
2733  // object elements.
2734  static void CopyElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from,
2735  uint32_t from_start, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to,
2736  ElementsKind from_kind, uint32_t to_start,
2737  int packed_size, int copy_size) {
2738  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2739  ElementsKind to_kind = KindTraits::Kind;
2740  switch (from_kind) {
2741  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2742  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2743  case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
2744  case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
2745  case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
2746  case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
2747  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
2748  case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
2749  case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
2750  case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
2751  case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
2752  CopyObjectToObjectElements(isolate, from, from_kind, from_start, to,
2753  to_kind, to_start, copy_size);
2754  break;
2755  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
2756  case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
2757  AllowGarbageCollection allow_allocation;
2758  DCHECK(IsObjectElementsKind(to_kind));
2759  CopyDoubleToObjectElements(isolate, from, from_start, to, to_start,
2760  copy_size);
2761  break;
2762  }
2763  case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS:
2764  CopyDictionaryToObjectElements(isolate, from, from_start, to, to_kind,
2765  to_start, copy_size);
2766  break;
2767  case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
2768  case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
2769  case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
2770  case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
2771 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) case TYPE##_ELEMENTS:
2772  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
2773  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
2774 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
2775  case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
2776  // This function is currently only used for JSArrays with non-zero
2777  // length.
2778  UNREACHABLE();
2779  case NO_ELEMENTS:
2780  break; // Nothing to do.
2781  }
2782  }
2783 
2784  static Maybe<bool> CollectValuesOrEntriesImpl(
2785  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
2786  DirectHandle<FixedArray> values_or_entries, bool get_entries,
2787  int* nof_items, PropertyFilter filter) {
2788  int count = 0;
2789  if (get_entries) {
2790  // Collecting entries needs to allocate, so this code must be handlified.
2791  DirectHandle<FixedArray> elements(Cast<FixedArray>(object->elements()),
2792  isolate);
2793  uint32_t length = elements->length();
2794  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < length; ++index) {
2795  InternalIndex entry(index);
2796  if (!Subclass::HasEntryImpl(isolate, *elements, entry)) continue;
2797  DirectHandle<Object> value =
2798  Subclass::GetImpl(isolate, *elements, entry);
2799  value = MakeEntryPair(isolate, index, value);
2800  values_or_entries->set(count++, *value);
2801  }
2802  } else {
2803  // No allocations here, so we can avoid handlification overhead.
2804  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2805  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(object->elements());
2806  uint32_t length = elements->length();
2807  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < length; ++index) {
2808  InternalIndex entry(index);
2809  if (!Subclass::HasEntryImpl(isolate, elements, entry)) continue;
2810  Tagged<Object> value = GetRaw(elements, entry);
2811  values_or_entries->set(count++, value);
2812  }
2813  }
2814  *nof_items = count;
2815  return Just(true);
2816  }
2817 
2818  static Maybe<int64_t> IndexOfValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
2819  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
2820  DirectHandle<Object> search_value,
2821  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
2822  DCHECK(JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *receiver));
2823  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2824  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements_base = receiver->elements();
2825  Tagged<Object> value = *search_value;
2826 
2827  if (start_from >= length) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
2828 
2829  length = std::min(static_cast<size_t>(elements_base->length()), length);
2830 
2831  // Only FAST_{,HOLEY_}ELEMENTS can store non-numbers.
2832  if (!IsNumber(value) && !IsObjectElementsKind(Subclass::kind()) &&
2833  !IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(Subclass::kind())) {
2834  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
2835  }
2836  // NaN can never be found by strict equality.
2837  if (IsNaN(value)) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
2838 
2839  // k can be greater than receiver->length() below, but it is bounded by
2840  // elements_base->length() so we never read out of bounds. This means that
2841  // elements->get(k) can return the hole, for which the StrictEquals will
2842  // always fail.
2843  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(receiver->elements());
2844  static_assert(FixedArray::kMaxLength <=
2845  std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
2846  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
2847  if (Object::StrictEquals(value,
2848  elements->get(static_cast<uint32_t>(k)))) {
2849  return Just<int64_t>(k);
2850  }
2851  }
2852  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
2853  }
2854 };

2902  // element logic instead of changing to dictionary mode.
2903  static Maybe<bool> SetLengthImpl(Isolate* isolate,
2904  DirectHandle<JSArray> array, uint32_t length,
2905  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
2906  uint32_t old_length = 0;
2907  CHECK(Object::ToArrayIndex(array->length(), &old_length));
2908  if (length == old_length) {
2909  // Do nothing.
2910  return Just(true);
2911  }
2912 
2913  // Transition to DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS.
2914  // Convert to dictionary mode.
2915  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> new_element_dictionary =
2916  old_length == 0
2917  ? isolate->factory()->empty_slow_element_dictionary()
2918  : array->GetElementsAccessor()->Normalize(isolate, array);
2919 
2920  // Migrate map.
2921  DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
2922  Map::Copy(isolate, direct_handle(array->map(), isolate),
2923  "SlowCopyForSetLengthImpl");
2924  new_map->set_is_extensible(false);
2925  new_map->set_elements_kind(DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS);
2926  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, array, new_map);
2927 
2928  if (!new_element_dictionary.is_null()) {
2929  array->set_elements(*new_element_dictionary);
2930  }
2931 
2932  if (array->elements() !=
2933  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_slow_element_dictionary()) {
2934  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary(array->element_dictionary(),
2935  isolate);
2936  // Make sure we never go back to the fast case
2937  array->RequireSlowElements(*dictionary);
2938  JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate),
2939  dictionary,
2940  PropertyAttributes::NONE);
2941  }
2942 
2943  // Set length.
2944  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> new_backing_store(array->elements(), isolate);
2945  return DictionaryElementsAccessor::SetLengthImpl(isolate, array, length,
2946  new_backing_store);
2947  }
2948 };

3199  : public FastElementsAccessor<Subclass, KindTraits> {
3200  public:

3202  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,

3214  InternalIndex entry, Tagged<Object> value) {
3215 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
3216  if (IsUndefined(value)) {
3217  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(backing_store)->set_undefined(entry.as_int());
3218  return;
3219  }
3220 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE

3232  static void CopyElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from,
3233  uint32_t from_start, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to,
3234  ElementsKind from_kind, uint32_t to_start,
3235  int packed_size, int copy_size) {
3236  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3237  switch (from_kind) {
3238  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
3239  CopyPackedSmiToDoubleElements(from, from_start, to, to_start,
3240  packed_size, copy_size);
3241  break;
3242  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
3243  CopySmiToDoubleElements(from, from_start, to, to_start, copy_size);
3244  break;
3245  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
3246  case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
3247  CopyDoubleToDoubleElements(from, from_start, to, to_start, copy_size);
3248  break;
3249  case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
3250  case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
3251  case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
3252  case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
3253  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
3254  case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
3255  case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
3256  case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
3257  case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
3258  CopyObjectToDoubleElements(from, from_start, to, to_start, copy_size);
3259  break;
3260  case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS:
3261  CopyDictionaryToDoubleElements(isolate, from, from_start, to, to_start,
3262  copy_size);
3263  break;
3264  case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
3265  case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
3266  case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
3267  case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
3268  case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
3269  case NO_ELEMENTS:
3270 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) case TYPE##_ELEMENTS:
3271  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
3272  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
3273 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
3274  // This function is currently only used for JSArrays with non-zero
3275  // length.
3276  UNREACHABLE();
3277  }
3278  }
3279 
3280  static Maybe<bool> CollectValuesOrEntriesImpl(
3281  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3282  DirectHandle<FixedArray> values_or_entries, bool get_entries,
3283  int* nof_items, PropertyFilter filter) {
3284  DirectHandle<FixedDoubleArray> elements(
3285  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(object->elements()), isolate);
3286  int count = 0;
3287  uint32_t length = elements->length();
3288  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < length; ++index) {
3289  InternalIndex entry(index);
3290  if (!Subclass::HasEntryImpl(isolate, *elements, entry)) continue;
3291  DirectHandle<Object> value = Subclass::GetImpl(isolate, *elements, entry);
3292  if (get_entries) {
3293  value = MakeEntryPair(isolate, index, value);
3294  }
3295  values_or_entries->set(count++, *value);
3296  }
3297  *nof_items = count;
3298  return Just(true);
3299  }
3300 
3301  static Maybe<int64_t> IndexOfValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
3302  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
3303  DirectHandle<Object> search_value,
3304  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
3305  DCHECK(JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *receiver));
3306  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3307  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements_base = receiver->elements();
3308  Tagged<Object> value = *search_value;
3309 
3310  length = std::min(static_cast<size_t>(elements_base->length()), length);
3311 
3312  if (start_from >= length) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3313 
3314  if (!IsNumber(value)) {
3315 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
3316  if (IsUndefined(value)) {
3317  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> elements =
3318  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(receiver->elements());
3319 
3320  static_assert(FixedDoubleArray::kMaxLength <=
3321  std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
3322  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
3323  int k_int = static_cast<int>(k);
3324  if (elements->is_undefined(k_int)) {
3325  return Just<int64_t>(k);
3326  }
3327  }
3328  }
3329 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
3330  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3331  }
3332  if (IsNaN(value)) {
3333  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3334  }
3335  double numeric_search_value = Object::NumberValue(value);
3336  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> elements =
3337  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(receiver->elements());
3338 
3339  static_assert(FixedDoubleArray::kMaxLength <=
3340  std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
3341  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
3342  int k_int = static_cast<int>(k);
3343  if (elements->is_the_hole(k_int)) {
3344  continue;
3345  }
3346  if (elements->get_scalar(k_int) == numeric_search_value) {
3347  return Just<int64_t>(k);
3348  }
3349  }
3350  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3351  }
3352 };

3364 enum IsSharedBuffer : bool { kShared = true, kUnshared = false };
3365 
3366 constexpr bool IsFloat16RawBitsZero(uint16_t x) {
3367  // IEEE754 comparison returns true for 0 == -0, even though they are two
3368  // different bit patterns.
3369  return (x & ~0x8000) == 0;
3370 }

3372 // Super class for all external element arrays.
3373 template <ElementsKind Kind, typename ElementType>
3374 class TypedElementsAccessor
3375  : public ElementsAccessorBase<TypedElementsAccessor<Kind, ElementType>,
3376  ElementsKindTraits<Kind>> {
3377  public:
3378  using BackingStore = typename ElementsKindTraits<Kind>::BackingStore;
3379  using AccessorClass = TypedElementsAccessor<Kind, ElementType>;
3380 
3381  // Conversions from (other) scalar values.
3382  static ElementType FromScalar(int value) {
3383  return static_cast<ElementType>(value);
3384  }
3385  static ElementType FromScalar(uint32_t value) {
3386  return static_cast<ElementType>(value);
3387  }
3388  static ElementType FromScalar(double value) {
3389  return FromScalar(DoubleToInt32(value));
3390  }
3391  static ElementType FromScalar(int64_t value) { UNREACHABLE(); }
3392  static ElementType FromScalar(uint64_t value) { UNREACHABLE(); }
3393 
3394  // Conversions from objects / handles.
3395  static ElementType FromObject(Tagged<Object> value,
3396  bool* lossless = nullptr) {
3397  if (IsSmi(value)) {
3398  return FromScalar(Smi::ToInt(value));
3399  } else if (IsHeapNumber(value)) {
3400  return FromScalar(Cast<HeapNumber>(value)->value());
3401  } else {
3402  // Clamp undefined here as well. All other types have been
3403  // converted to a number type further up in the call chain.
3404  DCHECK(IsUndefined(value));
3405  return FromScalar(Cast<Oddball>(value)->to_number_raw());
3406  }
3407  }
3408  static ElementType FromHandle(DirectHandle<Object> value,
3409  bool* lossless = nullptr) {
3410  return FromObject(*value, lossless);
3411  }
3412 
3413  // Conversion of scalar value to handlified object.
3414  static Handle<Object> ToHandle(Isolate* isolate, ElementType value);
3415 
3416  static void SetImpl(DirectHandle<JSObject> holder, InternalIndex entry,
3417  Tagged<Object> value) {
3418  auto typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(holder);
3419  DCHECK_LE(entry.raw_value(), typed_array->GetLength());
3420  auto* entry_ptr =
3421  static_cast<ElementType*>(typed_array->DataPtr()) + entry.raw_value();
3422  auto is_shared = typed_array->buffer()->is_shared() ? kShared : kUnshared;
3423  SetImpl(entry_ptr, FromObject(value), is_shared);
3424  }
3425 
3426  static void SetImpl(ElementType* data_ptr, ElementType value,
3427  IsSharedBuffer is_shared) {
3428  // TODO(ishell, v8:8875): Independent of pointer compression, 8-byte size
3429  // fields (external pointers, doubles and BigInt data) are not always 8-byte
3430  // aligned. This is relying on undefined behaviour in C++, since {data_ptr}
3431  // is not aligned to {alignof(ElementType)}.
3432  if (!is_shared) {
3433  base::WriteUnalignedValue(reinterpret_cast<Address>(data_ptr), value);
3434  return;
3435  }
3436 
3437  // The JavaScript memory model allows for racy reads and writes to a
3438  // SharedArrayBuffer's backing store. Using relaxed atomics is not strictly
3439  // required for JavaScript, but will avoid undefined behaviour in C++ and is
3440  // unlikely to introduce noticeable overhead.
3441  if (IsAligned(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(data_ptr),
3442  alignof(std::atomic<ElementType>))) {
3443  // Use a single relaxed atomic store.
3444  static_assert(sizeof(std::atomic<ElementType>) == sizeof(ElementType));
3445  reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<ElementType>*>(data_ptr)->store(
3446  value, std::memory_order_relaxed);
3447  return;
3448  }
3449 
3450  // Some static CHECKs (are optimized out if succeeding) to ensure that
3451  // {data_ptr} is at least four byte aligned, and {std::atomic<uint32_t>}
3452  // has size and alignment of four bytes, such that we can cast the
3453  // {data_ptr} to it.
3454  CHECK_LE(kInt32Size, alignof(ElementType));
3455  CHECK_EQ(kInt32Size, alignof(std::atomic<uint32_t>));
3456  CHECK_EQ(kInt32Size, sizeof(std::atomic<uint32_t>));
3457  // And dynamically check that we indeed have at least four byte alignment.
3458  DCHECK(IsAligned(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(data_ptr), kInt32Size));
3459  // Store as multiple 32-bit words. Make {kNumWords} >= 1 to avoid compiler
3460  // warnings for the empty array or memcpy to an empty object.
3461  constexpr size_t kNumWords =
3462  std::max(size_t{1}, sizeof(ElementType) / kInt32Size);
3463  uint32_t words[kNumWords];
3464  CHECK_EQ(sizeof(words), sizeof(value));
3465  memcpy(words, &value, sizeof(value));
3466  for (size_t word = 0; word < kNumWords; ++word) {
3467  static_assert(sizeof(std::atomic<uint32_t>) == sizeof(uint32_t));
3468  reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<uint32_t>*>(data_ptr)[word].store(
3469  words[word], std::memory_order_relaxed);
3470  }
3471  }
3472 
3473  static Handle<Object> GetInternalImpl(Isolate* isolate,
3474  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder,
3475  InternalIndex entry) {
3476  auto typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(holder);
3477  DCHECK_LT(entry.raw_value(), typed_array->GetLength());
3478  DCHECK(!typed_array->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds());
3479  auto* element_ptr =
3480  static_cast<ElementType*>(typed_array->DataPtr()) + entry.raw_value();
3481  auto is_shared = typed_array->buffer()->is_shared() ? kShared : kUnshared;
3482  ElementType elem = GetImpl(element_ptr, is_shared);
3483  return ToHandle(isolate, elem);
3484  }
3485 
3486  static DirectHandle<Object> GetImpl(Isolate* isolate,
3487  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
3488  InternalIndex entry) {
3489  UNREACHABLE();
3490  }
3491 
3492  static ElementType GetImpl(ElementType* data_ptr, IsSharedBuffer is_shared) {
3493  // TODO(ishell, v8:8875): Independent of pointer compression, 8-byte size
3494  // fields (external pointers, doubles and BigInt data) are not always
3495  // 8-byte aligned.
3496  if (!is_shared) {
3497  return base::ReadUnalignedValue<ElementType>(
3498  reinterpret_cast<Address>(data_ptr));
3499  }
3500 
3501  // The JavaScript memory model allows for racy reads and writes to a
3502  // SharedArrayBuffer's backing store. Using relaxed atomics is not strictly
3503  // required for JavaScript, but will avoid undefined behaviour in C++ and is
3504  // unlikely to introduce noticeable overhead.
3505  if (IsAligned(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(data_ptr),
3506  alignof(std::atomic<ElementType>))) {
3507  // Use a single relaxed atomic load.
3508  static_assert(sizeof(std::atomic<ElementType>) == sizeof(ElementType));
3509  // Note: acquire semantics are not needed here, but clang seems to merge
3510  // this atomic load with the non-atomic load above if we use relaxed
3511  // semantics. This will result in TSan failures.
3512  return reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<ElementType>*>(data_ptr)->load(
3513  std::memory_order_acquire);
3514  }
3515 
3516  // Some static CHECKs (are optimized out if succeeding) to ensure that
3517  // {data_ptr} is at least four byte aligned, and {std::atomic<uint32_t>}
3518  // has size and alignment of four bytes, such that we can cast the
3519  // {data_ptr} to it.
3520  CHECK_LE(kInt32Size, alignof(ElementType));
3521  CHECK_EQ(kInt32Size, alignof(std::atomic<uint32_t>));
3522  CHECK_EQ(kInt32Size, sizeof(std::atomic<uint32_t>));
3523  // And dynamically check that we indeed have at least four byte alignment.
3524  DCHECK(IsAligned(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(data_ptr), kInt32Size));
3525  // Load in multiple 32-bit words. Make {kNumWords} >= 1 to avoid compiler
3526  // warnings for the empty array or memcpy to an empty object.
3527  constexpr size_t kNumWords =
3528  std::max(size_t{1}, sizeof(ElementType) / kInt32Size);
3529  uint32_t words[kNumWords];
3530  for (size_t word = 0; word < kNumWords; ++word) {
3531  static_assert(sizeof(std::atomic<uint32_t>) == sizeof(uint32_t));
3532  words[word] =
3533  reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<uint32_t>*>(data_ptr)[word].load(
3534  std::memory_order_relaxed);
3535  }
3536  ElementType result;
3537  CHECK_EQ(sizeof(words), sizeof(result));
3538  memcpy(&result, words, sizeof(result));
3539  return result;
3540  }

3600 
3601  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus AddElementsToKeyAccumulatorImpl(
3602  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver, KeyAccumulator* accumulator,
3603  AddKeyConversion convert) {
3604  Isolate* isolate = accumulator->isolate();
3605  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements(receiver->elements(), isolate);
3606  size_t length = AccessorClass::GetCapacityImpl(*receiver, *elements);
3607  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
3608  DirectHandle<Object> value =
3609  AccessorClass::GetInternalImpl(isolate, receiver, InternalIndex(i));
3610  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(accumulator->AddKey(value, convert));
3611  }
3612  return ExceptionStatus::kSuccess;
3613  }
3614 
3615  static Maybe<bool> CollectValuesOrEntriesImpl(
3616  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3617  DirectHandle<FixedArray> values_or_entries, bool get_entries,
3618  int* nof_items, PropertyFilter filter) {
3619  int count = 0;
3620  if ((filter & ONLY_CONFIGURABLE) == 0) {
3621  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements(object->elements(), isolate);
3622  size_t length = AccessorClass::GetCapacityImpl(*object, *elements);
3623  for (size_t index = 0; index < length; ++index) {
3624  DirectHandle<Object> value = AccessorClass::GetInternalImpl(
3625  isolate, object, InternalIndex(index));
3626  if (get_entries) {
3627  value = MakeEntryPair(isolate, index, value);
3628  }
3629  values_or_entries->set(count++, *value);
3630  }
3631  }
3632  *nof_items = count;
3633  return Just(true);
3634  }
3635 
3636  static bool ToTypedSearchValue(double search_value,
3637  ElementType* typed_search_value) {
3638  if (!base::IsValueInRangeForNumericType<ElementType>(search_value) &&
3639  std::isfinite(search_value)) {
3640  // Return true if value can't be represented in this space.
3641  return true;
3642  }
3643  ElementType typed_value;
3644  if (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
3645  typed_value = fp16_ieee_from_fp32_value(static_cast<float>(search_value));
3646  *typed_search_value = typed_value;
3647  return (static_cast<double>(fp16_ieee_to_fp32_value(typed_value)) !=
3648  search_value); // Loss of precision.
3649  }
3650  typed_value = static_cast<ElementType>(search_value);
3651  *typed_search_value = typed_value;
3652  return static_cast<double>(typed_value) !=
3653  search_value; // Loss of precision.
3654  }
3655 
3656  static MaybeDirectHandle<Object> FillImpl(Isolate* isolate,
3657  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
3658  DirectHandle<Object> value,
3659  size_t start, size_t end) {
3660  DirectHandle<JSTypedArray> typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(receiver);
3661  DCHECK(!typed_array->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds());
3662  DCHECK_LE(start, end);
3663  DCHECK_LE(end, typed_array->GetLength());
3664  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3665  ElementType scalar = FromHandle(value);
3666  ElementType* data = static_cast<ElementType*>(typed_array->DataPtr());
3667  ElementType* first = data + start;
3668  ElementType* last = data + end;
3669  if (typed_array->buffer()->is_shared()) {
3670  // TypedArrays backed by shared buffers need to be filled using atomic
3671  // operations. Since 8-byte data are not currently always 8-byte aligned,
3672  // manually fill using SetImpl, which abstracts over alignment and atomic
3673  // complexities.
3674  for (; first != last; ++first) {
3675  AccessorClass::SetImpl(first, scalar, kShared);
3676  }
3677  } else if ((scalar == 0 && !(std::is_floating_point_v<ElementType> &&
3678  IsMinusZero(scalar))) ||
3679  (std::is_integral_v<ElementType> &&
3680  scalar == static_cast<ElementType>(-1))) {
3681  // As of 2022-06, this is faster than {std::fill}.
3682  // We could extend this to any {scalar} that's a pattern of repeating
3683  // bytes, but patterns other than 0 and -1 are probably rare.
3684  size_t num_bytes = static_cast<size_t>(reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(last) -
3685  reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(first));
3686  memset(first, static_cast<int8_t>(scalar), num_bytes);
3687  } else if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && alignof(ElementType) > kTaggedSize) {
3688  // TODO(ishell, v8:8875): See UnalignedSlot<T> for details.
3689  std::fill(UnalignedSlot<ElementType>(first),
3690  UnalignedSlot<ElementType>(last), scalar);
3691  } else {
3692  std::fill(first, last, scalar);
3693  }
3694  return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>(typed_array);
3695  }
3696 
3697  static Maybe<bool> IncludesValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
3698  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
3699  DirectHandle<Object> value,
3700  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
3701  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3702  Tagged<JSTypedArray> typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*receiver);
3703 
3704  bool out_of_bounds = false;
3705  size_t new_length = typed_array->GetLengthOrOutOfBounds(out_of_bounds);
3706  if (V8_UNLIKELY(out_of_bounds)) {
3707  return Just(IsUndefined(*value, isolate) && length > start_from);
3708  }
3709 
3710  // Prototype has no elements, and not searching for the hole --- limit
3711  // search to backing store length.
3712  if (new_length < length) {
3713  if (IsUndefined(*value, isolate) && length > start_from) {
3714  return Just(true);
3715  }
3716  length = new_length;
3717  }
3718 
3719  ElementType typed_search_value;
3720  ElementType* data_ptr =
3721  reinterpret_cast<ElementType*>(typed_array->DataPtr());
3722  auto is_shared = typed_array->buffer()->is_shared() ? kShared : kUnshared;
3723  if (Kind == BIGINT64_ELEMENTS || Kind == BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS ||
3724  Kind == RAB_GSAB_BIGINT64_ELEMENTS ||
3725  Kind == RAB_GSAB_BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS) {
3726  if (!IsBigInt(*value)) return Just(false);
3727  bool lossless;
3728  typed_search_value = FromHandle(value, &lossless);
3729  if (!lossless) return Just(false);
3730  } else {
3731  if (!IsNumber(*value)) return Just(false);
3732  double search_value = Object::NumberValue(*value);
3733  if (!std::isfinite(search_value)) {
3734  // Integral types cannot represent +Inf or NaN.
3735  if (!IsFloatTypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
3736  return Just(false);
3737  }
3738  if (std::isnan(search_value)) {
3739  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
3740  if (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
3741  float elem_k = fp16_ieee_to_fp32_value(
3742  AccessorClass::GetImpl(data_ptr + k, is_shared));
3743  if (std::isnan(elem_k)) return Just(true);
3744  } else {
3745  double elem_k = static_cast<double>(
3746  AccessorClass::GetImpl(data_ptr + k, is_shared));
3747  if (std::isnan(elem_k)) return Just(true);
3748  }
3749  }
3750  return Just(false);
3751  }
3752  } else if (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(Kind) && search_value == 0) {
3753  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
3754  ElementType elem_k = AccessorClass::GetImpl(data_ptr + k, is_shared);
3755  if (IsFloat16RawBitsZero(elem_k)) return Just(true);
3756  }
3757  return Just(false);
3758  }
3759 
3760  if (AccessorClass::ToTypedSearchValue(search_value,
3761  &typed_search_value)) {
3762  return Just(false);
3763  }
3764  }
3765 
3766  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
3767  ElementType elem_k = AccessorClass::GetImpl(data_ptr + k, is_shared);
3768  if (elem_k == typed_search_value) return Just(true);
3769  }
3770  return Just(false);
3771  }
3772 
3773  static Maybe<int64_t> IndexOfValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
3774  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
3775  DirectHandle<Object> value,
3776  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
3777  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3778  Tagged<JSTypedArray> typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*receiver);
3779 
3780  // If this is called via Array.prototype.indexOf (not
3781  // TypedArray.prototype.indexOf), it's possible that the TypedArray is
3782  // detached / out of bounds here.
3783  if (V8_UNLIKELY(typed_array->WasDetached())) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3784  bool out_of_bounds = false;
3785  size_t typed_array_length =
3786  typed_array->GetLengthOrOutOfBounds(out_of_bounds);
3787  if (V8_UNLIKELY(out_of_bounds)) {
3788  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3789  }
3790 
3791  // Prototype has no elements, and not searching for the hole --- limit
3792  // search to backing store length.
3793  if (typed_array_length < length) {
3794  length = typed_array_length;
3795  }
3796 
3797  auto is_shared = typed_array->buffer()->is_shared() ? kShared : kUnshared;
3798  ElementType typed_search_value;
3799 
3800  ElementType* data_ptr =
3801  reinterpret_cast<ElementType*>(typed_array->DataPtr());
3802  if (IsBigIntTypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
3803  if (!IsBigInt(*value)) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3804  bool lossless;
3805  typed_search_value = FromHandle(value, &lossless);
3806  if (!lossless) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3807  } else {
3808  if (!IsNumber(*value)) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3809  double search_value = Object::NumberValue(*value);
3810  if (!std::isfinite(search_value)) {
3811  // Integral types cannot represent +Inf or NaN.
3812  if (!IsFloatTypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
3813  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3814  }
3815  if (std::isnan(search_value)) {
3816  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3817  }
3818  } else if (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(Kind) && search_value == 0) {
3819  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
3820  ElementType elem_k = AccessorClass::GetImpl(data_ptr + k, is_shared);
3821  if (IsFloat16RawBitsZero(elem_k)) return Just<int64_t>(k);
3822  }
3823  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3824  }
3825  if (AccessorClass::ToTypedSearchValue(search_value,
3826  &typed_search_value)) {
3827  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3828  }
3829  }
3830 
3831  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
3832  ElementType elem_k = AccessorClass::GetImpl(data_ptr + k, is_shared);
3833  if (elem_k == typed_search_value) return Just<int64_t>(k);
3834  }
3835  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3836  }
3837 
3838  static Maybe<int64_t> LastIndexOfValueImpl(DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
3839  DirectHandle<Object> value,
3840  size_t start_from) {
3841  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3842  Tagged<JSTypedArray> typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*receiver);
3843  auto is_shared = typed_array->buffer()->is_shared() ? kShared : kUnshared;
3844 
3845  DCHECK(!typed_array->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds());
3846 
3847  ElementType typed_search_value;
3848 
3849  ElementType* data_ptr =
3850  reinterpret_cast<ElementType*>(typed_array->DataPtr());
3851  if (IsBigIntTypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
3852  if (!IsBigInt(*value)) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3853  bool lossless;
3854  typed_search_value = FromHandle(value, &lossless);
3855  if (!lossless) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3856  } else {
3857  if (!IsNumber(*value)) return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3858  double search_value = Object::NumberValue(*value);
3859  if (!std::isfinite(search_value)) {
3860  if (!IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(Kind) &&
3861  std::is_integral_v<ElementType>) {
3862  // Integral types cannot represent +Inf or NaN.
3863  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3864  } else if (std::isnan(search_value)) {
3865  // Strict Equality Comparison of NaN is always false.
3866  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3867  }
3868  }
3869  if (AccessorClass::ToTypedSearchValue(search_value,
3870  &typed_search_value)) {
3871  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3872  }
3873  }
3874 
3875  size_t typed_array_length = typed_array->GetLength();
3876  if (V8_UNLIKELY(start_from >= typed_array_length)) {
3877  // This can happen if the TypedArray got resized when we did ToInteger
3878  // on the last parameter of lastIndexOf.
3879  DCHECK(typed_array->IsVariableLength());
3880  if (typed_array_length == 0) {
3881  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3882  }
3883  start_from = typed_array_length - 1;
3884  }
3885 
3886  size_t k = start_from;
3887  do {
3888  ElementType elem_k = AccessorClass::GetImpl(data_ptr + k, is_shared);
3889  if constexpr (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
3890  if (IsFloat16RawBitsZero(typed_search_value) &&
3891  IsFloat16RawBitsZero(elem_k)) {
3892  return Just<int64_t>(k);
3893  }
3894  }
3895  if (elem_k == typed_search_value) return Just<int64_t>(k);
3896  } while (k-- != 0);
3897  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
3898  }
3899 
3900  static void ReverseImpl(Tagged<JSObject> receiver) {
3901  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3902  Tagged<JSTypedArray> typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(receiver);
3903 
3904  DCHECK(!typed_array->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds());
3905 
3906  size_t len = typed_array->GetLength();
3907  if (len == 0) return;
3908 
3909  ElementType* data = static_cast<ElementType*>(typed_array->DataPtr());
3910  if (typed_array->buffer()->is_shared()) {
3911  // TypedArrays backed by shared buffers need to be reversed using atomic
3912  // operations. Since 8-byte data are not currently always 8-byte aligned,
3913  // manually reverse using GetImpl and SetImpl, which abstract over
3914  // alignment and atomic complexities.
3915  for (ElementType *first = data, *last = data + len - 1; first < last;
3916  ++first, --last) {
3917  ElementType first_value = AccessorClass::GetImpl(first, kShared);
3918  ElementType last_value = AccessorClass::GetImpl(last, kShared);
3919  AccessorClass::SetImpl(first, last_value, kShared);
3920  AccessorClass::SetImpl(last, first_value, kShared);
3921  }
3922  } else if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && alignof(ElementType) > kTaggedSize) {
3923  // TODO(ishell, v8:8875): See UnalignedSlot<T> for details.
3924  std::reverse(UnalignedSlot<ElementType>(data),
3925  UnalignedSlot<ElementType>(data + len));
3926  } else {
3927  std::reverse(data, data + len);
3928  }
3929  }
3930 
3931  static Handle<FixedArray> CreateListFromArrayLikeImpl(
3932  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, uint32_t length) {
3933  DirectHandle<JSTypedArray> typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(object);
3934  Handle<FixedArray> result = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(length);
3935  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
3936  DirectHandle<Object> value = AccessorClass::GetInternalImpl(
3937  isolate, typed_array, InternalIndex(i));
3938  result->set(i, *value);
3939  }
3940  return result;
3941  }
3942 
3943  static void CopyTypedArrayElementsSliceImpl(Tagged<JSTypedArray> source,
3944  Tagged<JSTypedArray> destination,
3945  size_t start, size_t end) {
3946  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3947  DCHECK_EQ(destination->GetElementsKind(), AccessorClass::kind());
3948  CHECK(!source->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds());
3949  CHECK(!destination->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds());
3950  DCHECK_LE(start, end);
3951  DCHECK_LE(end, source->GetLength());
3952  size_t count = end - start;
3953  DCHECK_LE(count, destination->GetLength());
3954  ElementType* dest_data = static_cast<ElementType*>(destination->DataPtr());
3955  auto is_shared =
3956  source->buffer()->is_shared() || destination->buffer()->is_shared()
3957  ? kShared
3958  : kUnshared;
3959  switch (source->GetElementsKind()) {
3960 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
3961  case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: { \
3962  ctype* source_data = reinterpret_cast<ctype*>(source->DataPtr()) + start; \
3963  CopyBetweenBackingStores<TYPE##_ELEMENTS, ctype>(source_data, dest_data, \
3964  count, is_shared); \
3965  break; \
3966  }
3967  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
3968 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
3969 
3970 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype, NON_RAB_GSAB_TYPE) \
3971  case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: { \
3972  ctype* source_data = reinterpret_cast<ctype*>(source->DataPtr()) + start; \
3973  CopyBetweenBackingStores<NON_RAB_GSAB_TYPE##_ELEMENTS, ctype>( \
3974  source_data, dest_data, count, is_shared); \
3975  break; \
3976  }
3977  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS_WITH_NON_RAB_GSAB_ELEMENTS_KIND(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
3978 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
3979  default:
3980  UNREACHABLE();
3981  break;
3982  }
3983  }
3984 
3985  // TODO(v8:11111): Update this once we have external RAB / GSAB array types.
3986  static bool HasSimpleRepresentation(ExternalArrayType type) {
3987  return !(type == kExternalFloat32Array || type == kExternalFloat64Array ||
3988  type == kExternalUint8ClampedArray ||
3989  type == kExternalFloat16Array);
3990  }
3991 
3992  template <ElementsKind SourceKind, typename SourceElementType>
3993  static void CopyBetweenBackingStores(SourceElementType* source_data_ptr,
3994  ElementType* dest_data_ptr,
3995  size_t length,
3996  IsSharedBuffer is_shared) {
3997  CopyBetweenBackingStoresImpl<Kind, ElementType, SourceKind,
3998  SourceElementType>::Copy(source_data_ptr,
3999  dest_data_ptr, length,
4000  is_shared);
4001  }
4002 
4003  static void CopyElementsFromTypedArray(Tagged<JSTypedArray> source,
4004  Tagged<JSTypedArray> destination,
4005  size_t length, size_t offset) {
4006  // The source is a typed array, so we know we don't need to do ToNumber
4007  // side-effects, as the source elements will always be a number.
4008  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4009 
4010  CHECK(!source->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds());
4011  CHECK(!destination->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds());
4012 
4013  DCHECK_LE(offset, destination->GetLength());
4014  DCHECK_LE(length, destination->GetLength() - offset);
4015  DCHECK_LE(length, source->GetLength());
4016 
4017  ExternalArrayType source_type = source->type();
4018  ExternalArrayType destination_type = destination->type();
4019 
4020  bool same_type = source_type == destination_type;
4021  bool same_size = source->element_size() == destination->element_size();
4022  bool both_are_simple = HasSimpleRepresentation(source_type) &&
4023  HasSimpleRepresentation(destination_type);
4024 
4025  uint8_t* source_data = static_cast<uint8_t*>(source->DataPtr());
4026  uint8_t* dest_data = static_cast<uint8_t*>(destination->DataPtr());
4027  size_t source_byte_length = source->GetByteLength();
4028  size_t dest_byte_length = destination->GetByteLength();
4029 
4030  bool source_shared = source->buffer()->is_shared();
4031  bool destination_shared = destination->buffer()->is_shared();
4032 
4033  // We can simply copy the backing store if the types are the same, or if
4034  // we are converting e.g. Uint8 <-> Int8, as the binary representation
4035  // will be the same. This is not the case for floats or clamped Uint8,
4036  // which have special conversion operations.
4037  if (same_type || (same_size && both_are_simple)) {
4038  size_t element_size = source->element_size();
4039  if (source_shared || destination_shared) {
4040  base::Relaxed_Memcpy(
4041  reinterpret_cast<base::Atomic8*>(dest_data + offset * element_size),
4042  reinterpret_cast<base::Atomic8*>(source_data),
4043  length * element_size);
4044  } else {
4045  std::memmove(dest_data + offset * element_size, source_data,
4046  length * element_size);
4047  }
4048  } else {
4049  std::unique_ptr<uint8_t[]> cloned_source_elements;
4050 
4051  // If the typedarrays are overlapped, clone the source.
4052  if (dest_data + dest_byte_length > source_data &&
4053  source_data + source_byte_length > dest_data) {
4054  cloned_source_elements.reset(new uint8_t[source_byte_length]);
4055  if (source_shared) {
4056  base::Relaxed_Memcpy(
4057  reinterpret_cast<base::Atomic8*>(cloned_source_elements.get()),
4058  reinterpret_cast<base::Atomic8*>(source_data),
4059  source_byte_length);
4060  } else {
4061  std::memcpy(cloned_source_elements.get(), source_data,
4062  source_byte_length);
4063  }
4064  source_data = cloned_source_elements.get();
4065  }
4066 
4067  switch (source->GetElementsKind()) {
4068 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
4069  case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: \
4070  CopyBetweenBackingStores<TYPE##_ELEMENTS, ctype>( \
4071  reinterpret_cast<ctype*>(source_data), \
4072  reinterpret_cast<ElementType*>(dest_data) + offset, length, \
4073  source_shared || destination_shared ? kShared : kUnshared); \
4074  break;
4075  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
4076  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
4077  default:
4078  UNREACHABLE();
4079  break;
4080  }
4081 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
4082  }
4083  }
4084 
4085  static bool HoleyPrototypeLookupRequired(Isolate* isolate,
4086  Tagged<Context> context,
4087  Tagged<JSArray> source) {
4088  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4089  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
4090 
4091 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_FORCE_SLOW_PATH
4092  if (isolate->force_slow_path()) return true;
4093 #endif
4094 
4095  Tagged<Object> source_proto = source->map()->prototype();
4096 
4097  // Null prototypes are OK - we don't need to do prototype chain lookups on
4098  // them.
4099  if (IsNull(source_proto, isolate)) return false;
4100  if (IsJSProxy(source_proto)) return true;
4101  if (IsJSObject(source_proto) &&
4102  !context->native_context()->is_initial_array_prototype(
4103  Cast<JSObject>(source_proto))) {
4104  return true;
4105  }
4106 
4107  return !Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(isolate);
4108  }
4109 
4110  static bool TryCopyElementsFastNumber(Tagged<Context> context,
4111  Tagged<JSArray> source,
4112  Tagged<JSTypedArray> destination,
4113  size_t length, size_t offset) {
4114  if (IsBigIntTypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) return false;
4115  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
4116  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4117  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
4118 
4119  CHECK(!destination->WasDetached());
4120  bool out_of_bounds = false;
4121  CHECK_GE(destination->GetLengthOrOutOfBounds(out_of_bounds), length);
4122  CHECK(!out_of_bounds);
4123 
4124  size_t current_length;
4125  DCHECK(IsNumber(source->length()) &&
4126  TryNumberToSize(source->length(), &current_length) &&
4127  length <= current_length);
4128  USE(current_length);
4129 
4130  size_t dest_length = destination->GetLength();
4131  DCHECK(length + offset <= dest_length);
4132  USE(dest_length);
4133 
4134  ElementsKind kind = source->GetElementsKind();
4135 
4136  auto destination_shared =
4137  destination->buffer()->is_shared() ? kShared : kUnshared;
4138 
4139  // When we find the hole, we normally have to look up the element on the
4140  // prototype chain, which is not handled here and we return false instead.
4141  // When the array has the original array prototype, and that prototype has
4142  // not been changed in a way that would affect lookups, we can just convert
4143  // the hole into undefined.
4144  if (HoleyPrototypeLookupRequired(isolate, context, source)) return false;
4145 
4146  Tagged<Oddball> undefined = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value();
4147  ElementType* dest_data =
4148  reinterpret_cast<ElementType*>(destination->DataPtr()) + offset;
4149 
4150  // Fast-path for packed Smi kind.
4151  if (kind == PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
4152  Tagged<FixedArray> source_store = Cast<FixedArray>(source->elements());
4153 
4154  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4155  Tagged<Object> elem = source_store->get(static_cast<int>(i));
4156  ElementType elem_k;
4157  if (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
4158  elem_k = fp16_ieee_from_fp32_value(Smi::ToInt(elem));
4159  } else {
4160  elem_k = FromScalar(Smi::ToInt(elem));
4161  }
4162  SetImpl(dest_data + i, elem_k, destination_shared);
4163  }
4164  return true;
4165  } else if (kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
4166  Tagged<FixedArray> source_store = Cast<FixedArray>(source->elements());
4167  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4168  if (source_store->is_the_hole(isolate, static_cast<int>(i))) {
4169  SetImpl(dest_data + i, FromObject(undefined), destination_shared);
4170  } else {
4171  Tagged<Object> elem = source_store->get(static_cast<int>(i));
4172  ElementType elem_k;
4173  if (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
4174  elem_k = fp16_ieee_from_fp32_value(Smi::ToInt(elem));
4175  } else {
4176  elem_k = FromScalar(Smi::ToInt(elem));
4177  }
4178  SetImpl(dest_data + i, elem_k, destination_shared);
4179  }
4180  }
4181  return true;
4182  } else if (kind == PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
4183  // Fast-path for packed double kind. We avoid boxing and then immediately
4184  // unboxing the double here by using get_scalar.
4185  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> source_store =
4186  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(source->elements());
4187 
4188  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4189  // Use the from_double conversion for this specific TypedArray type,
4190  // rather than relying on C++ to convert elem.
4191  double elem = source_store->get_scalar(static_cast<int>(i));
4192  SetImpl(dest_data + i, FromScalar(elem), destination_shared);
4193  }
4194  return true;
4195  } else if (kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
4196  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> source_store =
4197  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(source->elements());
4198  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4199  if (source_store->is_the_hole(static_cast<int>(i))
4200 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
4201  || source_store->is_undefined(static_cast<int>(i))
4202 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
4203  ) {
4204  SetImpl(dest_data + i, FromObject(undefined), destination_shared);
4205  } else {
4206  double elem = source_store->get_scalar(static_cast<int>(i));
4207  SetImpl(dest_data + i, FromScalar(elem), destination_shared);
4208  }
4209  }
4210  return true;
4211  }
4212  return false;
4213  }
4214 
4215  // ES#sec-settypedarrayfromarraylike
4216  static Tagged<Object> CopyElementsHandleSlow(
4217  DirectHandle<JSAny> source, DirectHandle<JSTypedArray> destination,
4218  size_t length, size_t offset) {
4219  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
4220  // 8. Let k be 0.
4221  // 9. Repeat, while k < srcLength,
4222  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4223  DirectHandle<Object> elem;
4224  // a. Let Pk be ! ToString((k)).
4225  // b. Let value be ? Get(src, Pk).
4226  LookupIterator it(isolate, source, i);
4227  ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, elem,
4228  Object::GetProperty(&it));
4229  // c. Let targetIndex be (targetOffset + k).
4230  // d. Perform ? IntegerIndexedElementSet(target, targetIndex, value).
4231  //
4232  // Rest of loop body inlines ES#IntegerIndexedElementSet
4233  if (IsBigIntTypedArrayElementsKind(Kind)) {
4234  // 1. If O.[[ContentType]] is BigInt, let numValue be ? ToBigInt(value).
4235  ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, elem,
4236  BigInt::FromObject(isolate, elem));
4237  } else {
4238  // 2. Otherwise, let numValue be ? ToNumber(value).
4239  ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, elem,
4240  Object::ToNumber(isolate, elem));
4241  }
4242  // 3. If IsValidIntegerIndex(O, index) is true, then
4243  // a. Let offset be O.[[ByteOffset]].
4244  // b. Let elementSize be TypedArrayElementSize(O).
4245  // c. Let indexedPosition be ((index) elementSize) + offset.
4246  // d. Let elementType be TypedArrayElementType(O).
4247  // e. Perform SetValueInBuffer(O.[[ViewedArrayBuffer]],
4248  // indexedPosition, elementType, numValue, true, Unordered).
4249  bool out_of_bounds = false;
4250  size_t new_length = destination->GetLengthOrOutOfBounds(out_of_bounds);
4251  if (V8_UNLIKELY(out_of_bounds || destination->WasDetached() ||
4252  new_length <= offset + i)) {
4253  // Proceed with the loop so that we call get getters for the source even
4254  // though we don't set the values in the target.
4255  continue;
4256  }
4257  SetImpl(destination, InternalIndex(offset + i), *elem);
4258  // e. Set k to k + 1.
4259  }
4260  // 10. Return unused.
4261  return *isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
4262  }
4263 
4264  // This doesn't guarantee that the destination array will be completely
4265  // filled. The caller must do this by passing a source with equal length, if
4266  // that is required.
4267  static Tagged<Object> CopyElementsHandleImpl(
4268  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSAny> source,
4269  DirectHandle<JSObject> destination, size_t length, size_t offset) {
4270  if (length == 0) return *isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
4271 
4272  DirectHandle<JSTypedArray> destination_ta = Cast<JSTypedArray>(destination);
4273 
4274  // All conversions from TypedArrays can be done without allocation.
4275  if (IsJSTypedArray(*source)) {
4276  CHECK(!destination_ta->WasDetached());
4277  bool out_of_bounds = false;
4278  CHECK_LE(offset + length,
4279  destination_ta->GetLengthOrOutOfBounds(out_of_bounds));
4280  CHECK(!out_of_bounds);
4281  auto source_ta = Cast<JSTypedArray>(source);
4282  ElementsKind source_kind = source_ta->GetElementsKind();
4283  bool source_is_bigint = IsBigIntTypedArrayElementsKind(source_kind);
4284  bool target_is_bigint = IsBigIntTypedArrayElementsKind(Kind);
4285  // If we have to copy more elements than we have in the source, we need to
4286  // do special handling and conversion; that happens in the slow case.
4287  if (source_is_bigint == target_is_bigint && !source_ta->WasDetached() &&
4288  length + offset <= source_ta->GetLength()) {
4289  CopyElementsFromTypedArray(*source_ta, *destination_ta, length, offset);
4290  return *isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
4291  }
4292  } else if (IsJSArray(*source)) {
4293  CHECK(!destination_ta->WasDetached());
4294  bool out_of_bounds = false;
4295  CHECK_LE(offset + length,
4296  destination_ta->GetLengthOrOutOfBounds(out_of_bounds));
4297  CHECK(!out_of_bounds);
4298  // Fast cases for packed numbers kinds where we don't need to allocate.
4299  auto source_js_array = Cast<JSArray>(source);
4300  size_t current_length;
4301  DCHECK(IsNumber(source_js_array->length()));
4302  if (TryNumberToSize(source_js_array->length(), &current_length) &&
4303  length <= current_length) {
4304  auto source_array = Cast<JSArray>(source);
4305  if (TryCopyElementsFastNumber(isolate->context(), *source_array,
4306  *destination_ta, length, offset)) {
4307  return *isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
4308  }
4309  }
4310  }
4311  // Final generic case that handles prototype chain lookups, getters, proxies
4312  // and observable side effects via valueOf, etc. In this case, it's possible
4313  // that the length getter detached / resized the underlying buffer.
4314  return CopyElementsHandleSlow(source, destination_ta, length, offset);
4315  }
4316 };
4317 
4318 template <ElementsKind Kind, typename ElementType, ElementsKind SourceKind,
4319  typename SourceElementType>
4320 struct CopyBetweenBackingStoresImpl {
4321  static void Copy(SourceElementType* source_data_ptr,
4322  ElementType* dest_data_ptr, size_t length,
4323  IsSharedBuffer is_shared) {
4324  for (; length > 0; --length, ++source_data_ptr, ++dest_data_ptr) {
4325  // We use scalar accessors to avoid boxing/unboxing, so there are no
4326  // allocations.
4327  SourceElementType source_elem =
4328  TypedElementsAccessor<SourceKind, SourceElementType>::GetImpl(
4329  source_data_ptr, is_shared);
4330  ElementType dest_elem =
4331  TypedElementsAccessor<Kind, ElementType>::FromScalar(source_elem);
4332 
4333  TypedElementsAccessor<Kind, ElementType>::SetImpl(dest_data_ptr,
4334  dest_elem, is_shared);
4335  }
4336  }
4337 };
4338 
4339 namespace {
4340 template <ElementsKind DestKind, typename DestElementType,
4341  ElementsKind SourceKind>
4342 void CopyFromFloat16BackingStore(uint16_t* source_data_ptr,
4343  DestElementType* dest_data_ptr, size_t length,
4344  IsSharedBuffer is_shared) {
4345  for (; length > 0; --length, ++source_data_ptr, ++dest_data_ptr) {
4346  // We use scalar accessors to avoid boxing/unboxing, so there are no
4347  // allocations.
4348  uint16_t source_elem = TypedElementsAccessor<SourceKind, uint16_t>::GetImpl(
4349  source_data_ptr, is_shared);
4350  DestElementType dest_elem;
4351  if constexpr (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(DestKind)) {
4352  // There is the reasonable expectations that copying to the same kind of
4353  // TypedArray does not change the bit pattern of the data. For float16,
4354  // round tripping fp16->fp32->fp16 with the software emulation can change
4355  // NaN patterns.
4356  dest_elem = source_elem;
4357  } else {
4358  dest_elem = TypedElementsAccessor<DestKind, DestElementType>::FromScalar(
4359  fp16_ieee_to_fp32_value(source_elem));
4360  }
4361 
4362  TypedElementsAccessor<DestKind, DestElementType>::SetImpl(
4363  dest_data_ptr, dest_elem, is_shared);
4364  }
4365 }
4366 } // namespace
4367 
4368 template <ElementsKind Kind, typename ElementType>
4369 struct CopyBetweenBackingStoresImpl<Kind, ElementType, FLOAT16_ELEMENTS,
4370  uint16_t> {
4371  static void Copy(uint16_t* source_data_ptr, ElementType* dest_data_ptr,
4372  size_t length, IsSharedBuffer is_shared) {
4373  CopyFromFloat16BackingStore<Kind, ElementType, FLOAT16_ELEMENTS>(
4374  source_data_ptr, dest_data_ptr, length, is_shared);
4375  }
4376 };

4382  size_t length, IsSharedBuffer is_shared) {
4383  CopyFromFloat16BackingStore<Kind, ElementType, RAB_GSAB_FLOAT16_ELEMENTS>(
4384  source_data_ptr, dest_data_ptr, length, is_shared);
