4863 #define FIXED_ELEMENTS_ACCESSOR(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
4864  using Type##ElementsAccessor = TypedElementsAccessor<TYPE##_ELEMENTS, ctype>;
4865 TYPED_ARRAYS(FIXED_ELEMENTS_ACCESSOR)
4866 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(FIXED_ELEMENTS_ACCESSOR)
4867 #undef FIXED_ELEMENTS_ACCESSOR
4868 
4869 template <typename Subclass, typename ArgumentsAccessor, typename KindTraits>
4870 class SloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor
4871  : public ElementsAccessorBase<Subclass, KindTraits> {
4872  public:
4873  static void ConvertArgumentsStoreResult(
4874  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements,
4875  DirectHandle<Object> result) {
4876  UNREACHABLE();
4877  }
4878 
4879  static Handle<Object> GetImpl(Isolate* isolate,
4880  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> parameters,
4881  InternalIndex entry) {
4882  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements(
4883  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(parameters), isolate);
4884  uint32_t length = elements->length();
4885  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
4886  // Read context mapped entry.
4887  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4888  Tagged<Object> probe =
4889  elements->mapped_entries(entry.as_uint32(), kRelaxedLoad);
4890  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(probe, isolate));
4891  Tagged<Context> context = elements->context();
4892  int context_entry = Smi::ToInt(probe);
4893  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(context->GetNoCell(context_entry), isolate));
4894  return handle(context->GetNoCell(context_entry), isolate);
4895  } else {
4896  // Entry is not context mapped, defer to the arguments.
4897  Handle<Object> result = ArgumentsAccessor::GetImpl(
4898  isolate, elements->arguments(), entry.adjust_down(length));
4899  return Subclass::ConvertArgumentsStoreResult(isolate, elements, result);
4900  }
4901  }
4902 
4903  static void TransitionElementsKindImpl(Isolate* isolate,
4904  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4905  DirectHandle<Map> map) {
4906  UNREACHABLE();
4907  }
4908 
4909  static Maybe<bool> GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(Isolate* isolate,
4910  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4911  uint32_t capacity) {
4912  UNREACHABLE();
4913  }
4914 
4915  static inline void SetImpl(DirectHandle<JSObject> holder, InternalIndex entry,
4916  Tagged<Object> value) {
4917  SetImpl(holder->elements(), entry, value);
4918  }
4919 
4920  static inline void SetImpl(Tagged<FixedArrayBase> store, InternalIndex entry,
4921  Tagged<Object> value) {
4922  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
4923  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(store);
4924  uint32_t length = elements->length();
4925  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
4926  // Store context mapped entry.
4927  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4928  Tagged<Object> probe =
4929  elements->mapped_entries(entry.as_uint32(), kRelaxedLoad);
4930  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(probe));
4931  Tagged<Context> context = Cast<Context>(elements->context());
4932  int context_entry = Smi::ToInt(probe);
4933  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(context->GetNoCell(context_entry)));
4934  context->SetNoCell(context_entry, value);
4935  } else {
4936  // Entry is not context mapped defer to arguments.
4937  Tagged<FixedArray> arguments = elements->arguments();
4938  Tagged<Object> current =
4939  ArgumentsAccessor::GetRaw(arguments, entry.adjust_down(length));
4940  if (IsAliasedArgumentsEntry(current)) {
4941  Tagged<AliasedArgumentsEntry> alias =
4942  Cast<AliasedArgumentsEntry>(current);
4943  Tagged<Context> context = Cast<Context>(elements->context());
4944  int context_entry = alias->aliased_context_slot();
4945  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(context->GetNoCell(context_entry)));
4946  context->SetNoCell(context_entry, value);
4947  } else {
4948  ArgumentsAccessor::SetImpl(arguments, entry.adjust_down(length), value);
4949  }
4950  }
4951  }
4952 
4953  static Maybe<bool> SetLengthImpl(Isolate* isolate,
4954  DirectHandle<JSArray> array, uint32_t length,
4955  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> parameter_map) {
4956  // Sloppy arguments objects are not arrays.
4957  UNREACHABLE();
4958  }
4959 
4960  static uint32_t GetCapacityImpl(Tagged<JSObject> holder,
4961  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> store) {
4962  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
4963  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(store);
4964  Tagged<FixedArray> arguments = elements->arguments();
4965  return elements->length() +
4966  ArgumentsAccessor::GetCapacityImpl(holder, arguments);
4967  }
4968 
4969  static uint32_t GetMaxNumberOfEntries(Isolate* isolate,
4970  Tagged<JSObject> holder,
4971  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
4972  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
4973  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(backing_store);
4974  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> arguments = elements->arguments();
4975  size_t max_entries =
4976  ArgumentsAccessor::GetMaxNumberOfEntries(isolate, holder, arguments);
4977  DCHECK_LE(max_entries, std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
4978  return elements->length() + static_cast<uint32_t>(max_entries);
4979  }
4980 
4981  static uint32_t NumberOfElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate,
4982  Tagged<JSObject> receiver,
4983  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
4984  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
4985  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(backing_store);
4986  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> arguments = elements->arguments();
4987  uint32_t nof_elements = 0;
4988  uint32_t length = elements->length();
4989  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < length; index++) {
4990  if (HasParameterMapArg(isolate, elements, index)) nof_elements++;
4991  }
4992  return nof_elements + ArgumentsAccessor::NumberOfElementsImpl(
4993  isolate, receiver, arguments);
4994  }
4995 
4996  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus AddElementsToKeyAccumulatorImpl(
4997  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver, KeyAccumulator* accumulator,
4998  AddKeyConversion convert) {
4999  Isolate* isolate = accumulator->isolate();
5000  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements(receiver->elements(), isolate);
5001  uint32_t length = GetCapacityImpl(*receiver, *elements);
5002  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < length; index++) {
5003  InternalIndex entry(index);
5004  if (!HasEntryImpl(isolate, *elements, entry)) continue;
5005  DirectHandle<Object> value = GetImpl(isolate, *elements, entry);
5006  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(accumulator->AddKey(value, convert));
5007  }
5008  return ExceptionStatus::kSuccess;
5009  }
5010 
5011  static bool HasEntryImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> parameters,
5012  InternalIndex entry) {
5013  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
5014  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(parameters);
5015  uint32_t length = elements->length();
5016  if (entry.raw_value() < length) {
5017  return HasParameterMapArg(isolate, elements, entry.raw_value());
5018  }
5019  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> arguments = elements->arguments();
5020  return ArgumentsAccessor::HasEntryImpl(isolate, arguments,
5021  entry.adjust_down(length));
5022  }
5023 
5024  static bool HasAccessorsImpl(Tagged<JSObject> holder,
5025  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
5026  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
5027  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(backing_store);
5028  Tagged<FixedArray> arguments = elements->arguments();
5029  return ArgumentsAccessor::HasAccessorsImpl(holder, arguments);
5030  }
5031 
5032  static InternalIndex GetEntryForIndexImpl(Isolate* isolate,
5033  Tagged<JSObject> holder,
5034  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> parameters,
5035  size_t index,
5036  PropertyFilter filter) {
5037  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
5038  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(parameters);
5039  if (HasParameterMapArg(isolate, elements, index)) {
5040  return InternalIndex(index);
5041  }
5042  Tagged<FixedArray> arguments = elements->arguments();
5043  InternalIndex entry = ArgumentsAccessor::GetEntryForIndexImpl(
5044  isolate, holder, arguments, index, filter);
5045  if (entry.is_not_found()) return entry;
5046  // Arguments entries could overlap with the dictionary entries, hence offset
5047  // them by the number of context mapped entries.
5048  return entry.adjust_up(elements->length());
5049  }
5050 
5051  static PropertyDetails GetDetailsImpl(Tagged<JSObject> holder,
5052  InternalIndex entry) {
5053  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
5054  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(holder->elements());
5055  uint32_t length = elements->length();
5056  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5057  return PropertyDetails(PropertyKind::kData, NONE,
5058  PropertyCellType::kNoCell);
5059  }
5060  Tagged<FixedArray> arguments = elements->arguments();
5061  return ArgumentsAccessor::GetDetailsImpl(arguments,
5062  entry.adjust_down(length));
5063  }
5064 
5065  static bool HasParameterMapArg(Isolate* isolate,
5066  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements,
5067  size_t index) {
5068  uint32_t length = elements->length();
5069  if (index >= length) return false;
5070  return !IsTheHole(
5071  elements->mapped_entries(static_cast<uint32_t>(index), kRelaxedLoad),
5072  isolate);
5073  }
5074 
5075  static void DeleteImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
5076  InternalIndex entry) {
5077  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements(
5078  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(obj->elements()), isolate);
5079  uint32_t length = elements->length();
5080  InternalIndex delete_or_entry = entry;
5081  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5082  delete_or_entry = InternalIndex::NotFound();
5083  }
5084  Subclass::SloppyDeleteImpl(isolate, obj, elements, delete_or_entry);
5085  // SloppyDeleteImpl allocates a new dictionary elements store. For making
5086  // heap verification happy we postpone clearing out the mapped entry.
5087  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5088  elements->set_mapped_entries(entry.as_uint32(),
5089  GetReadOnlyRoots().the_hole_value());
5090  }
5091  }
5092 
5093  static void SloppyDeleteImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
5094  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements,
5095  InternalIndex entry) {
5096  // Implemented in subclasses.
5097  UNREACHABLE();
5098  }
5099 
5100  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus CollectElementIndicesImpl(
5101  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
5102  KeyAccumulator* keys) {
5103  Isolate* isolate = keys->isolate();
5104  uint32_t nof_indices = 0;
5105  Handle<FixedArray> indices = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
5106  GetCapacityImpl(*object, *backing_store));
5107  DirectCollectElementIndicesImpl(isolate, object, backing_store,
5108  GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers,
5109  ENUMERABLE_STRINGS, indices, &nof_indices);
5110  SortIndices(isolate, indices, nof_indices);
5111  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < nof_indices; i++) {
5112  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(keys->AddKey(indices->get(i)));
5113  }
5114  return ExceptionStatus::kSuccess;
5115  }
5116 
5117  static Handle<FixedArray> DirectCollectElementIndicesImpl(
5118  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5119  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store, GetKeysConversion convert,
5120  PropertyFilter filter, Handle<FixedArray> list, uint32_t* nof_indices,
5121  uint32_t insertion_index = 0) {
5122  auto elements = Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(backing_store);
5123  uint32_t length = elements->length();
5124 
5125  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
5126  if (IsTheHole(elements->mapped_entries(i, kRelaxedLoad), isolate))
5127  continue;
5128  if (convert == GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString) {
5129  DirectHandle<String> index_string =
5130  isolate->factory()->Uint32ToString(i);
5131  list->set(insertion_index, *index_string);
5132  } else {
5133  list->set(insertion_index, Smi::FromInt(i));
5134  }
5135  insertion_index++;
5136  }
5137 
5138  DirectHandle<FixedArray> store(elements->arguments(), isolate);
5139  return ArgumentsAccessor::DirectCollectElementIndicesImpl(
5140  isolate, object, store, convert, filter, list, nof_indices,
5141  insertion_index);
5142  }
5143 
5144  static Maybe<bool> IncludesValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
5145  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5146  DirectHandle<Object> value,
5147  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
5148  DCHECK(JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *object));
5149  DirectHandle<Map> original_map(object->map(), isolate);
5150  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements(
5151  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(object->elements()), isolate);
5152  bool search_for_hole = IsUndefined(*value, isolate);
5153 
5154  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
5155  DCHECK_EQ(object->map(), *original_map);
5156  InternalIndex entry =
5157  GetEntryForIndexImpl(isolate, *object, *elements, k, ALL_PROPERTIES);
5158  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
5159  if (search_for_hole) return Just(true);
5160  continue;
5161  }
5162 
5163  DirectHandle<Object> element_k =
5164  Subclass::GetImpl(isolate, *elements, entry);
5165 
5166  if (IsAccessorPair(*element_k)) {
5167  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, k, LookupIterator::OWN);
5168  DCHECK(it.IsFound());
5169  DCHECK_EQ(it.state(), LookupIterator::ACCESSOR);
5170  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, element_k,
5171  Object::GetPropertyWithAccessor(&it),
5172  Nothing<bool>());
5173 
5174  if (Object::SameValueZero(*value, *element_k)) return Just(true);
5175 
5176  if (object->map() != *original_map) {
5177  // Some mutation occurred in accessor. Abort "fast" path
5178  return IncludesValueSlowPath(isolate, object, value, k + 1, length);
5179  }
5180  } else if (Object::SameValueZero(*value, *element_k)) {
5181  return Just(true);
5182  }
5183  }
5184  return Just(false);
5185  }
5186 
5187  static Maybe<int64_t> IndexOfValueImpl(Isolate* isolate,
5188  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5189  DirectHandle<Object> value,
5190  size_t start_from, size_t length) {
5191  DCHECK(JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *object));
5192  DirectHandle<Map> original_map(object->map(), isolate);
5193  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements(
5194  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(object->elements()), isolate);
5195 
5196  for (size_t k = start_from; k < length; ++k) {
5197  DCHECK_EQ(object->map(), *original_map);
5198  InternalIndex entry =
5199  GetEntryForIndexImpl(isolate, *object, *elements, k, ALL_PROPERTIES);
5200  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
5201  continue;
5202  }
5203 
5204  DirectHandle<Object> element_k =
5205  Subclass::GetImpl(isolate, *elements, entry);
5206 
5207  if (IsAccessorPair(*element_k)) {
5208  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, k, LookupIterator::OWN);
5209  DCHECK(it.IsFound());
5210  DCHECK_EQ(it.state(), LookupIterator::ACCESSOR);
5211  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, element_k,
5212  Object::GetPropertyWithAccessor(&it),
5213  Nothing<int64_t>());
5214 
5215  if (Object::StrictEquals(*value, *element_k)) {
5216  return Just<int64_t>(k);
5217  }
5218 
5219  if (object->map() != *original_map) {
5220  // Some mutation occurred in accessor. Abort "fast" path.
5221  return IndexOfValueSlowPath(isolate, object, value, k + 1, length);
5222  }
5223  } else if (Object::StrictEquals(*value, *element_k)) {
5224  return Just<int64_t>(k);
5225  }
5226  }
5227  return Just<int64_t>(-1);
5228  }
5229 };
5230 
5231 class SlowSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor
5232  : public SloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor<
5233  SlowSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor, DictionaryElementsAccessor,
5234  ElementsKindTraits<SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS>> {
5235  public:
5236  static Handle<Object> ConvertArgumentsStoreResult(
5237  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements,
5238  Handle<Object> result) {
5239  // Elements of the arguments object in slow mode might be slow aliases.
5240  if (IsAliasedArgumentsEntry(*result)) {
5241  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5242  Tagged<AliasedArgumentsEntry> alias =
5243  Cast<AliasedArgumentsEntry>(*result);
5244  Tagged<Context> context = elements->context();
5245  int context_entry = alias->aliased_context_slot();
5246  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(context->GetNoCell(context_entry), isolate));
5247  return handle(context->GetNoCell(context_entry), isolate);
5248  }
5249  return result;
5250  }
5251  static void SloppyDeleteImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
5252  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements,
5253  InternalIndex entry) {
5254  // No need to delete a context mapped entry from the arguments elements.
5255  if (entry.is_not_found()) return;
5256  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dict(
5257  Cast<NumberDictionary>(elements->arguments()), isolate);
5258  uint32_t length = elements->length();
5259  dict =
5260  NumberDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, dict, entry.adjust_down(length));
5261  elements->set_arguments(*dict);
5262  }
5263  static Maybe<bool> AddImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5264  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
5265  PropertyAttributes attributes,
5266  uint32_t new_capacity) {
5267  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements(
5268  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(object->elements()), isolate);
5269  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> old_arguments(elements->arguments(), isolate);
5270  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
5271  IsNumberDictionary(*old_arguments)
5272  ? Cast<NumberDictionary>(old_arguments)
5273  : JSObject::NormalizeElements(isolate, object);
5274  PropertyDetails details(PropertyKind::kData, attributes,
5275  PropertyCellType::kNoCell);
5276  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> new_dictionary =
5277  NumberDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, index, value, details);
5278  if (attributes != NONE) object->RequireSlowElements(*new_dictionary);
5279  if (*dictionary != *new_dictionary) {
5280  elements->set_arguments(*new_dictionary);
5281  }
5282  return Just(true);
5283  }
5284 
5285  static void ReconfigureImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5286  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> store,
5287  InternalIndex entry, DirectHandle<Object> value,
5288  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
5289  auto elements = Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(store);
5290  uint32_t length = elements->length();
5291  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5292  Tagged<Object> probe =
5293  elements->mapped_entries(entry.as_uint32(), kRelaxedLoad);
5294  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(probe, isolate));
5295  Tagged<Context> context = elements->context();
5296  int context_entry = Smi::ToInt(probe);
5297  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(context->GetNoCell(context_entry), isolate));
5298  context->SetNoCell(context_entry, *value);
5299 
5300  // Redefining attributes of an aliased element destroys fast aliasing.
5301  elements->set_mapped_entries(entry.as_uint32(),
5302  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).the_hole_value());
5303  // For elements that are still writable we re-establish slow aliasing.
5304  if ((attributes & READ_ONLY) == 0) {
5305  value = isolate->factory()->NewAliasedArgumentsEntry(context_entry);
5306  }
5307 
5308  PropertyDetails details(PropertyKind::kData, attributes,
5309  PropertyCellType::kNoCell);
5310  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> arguments(
5311  Cast<NumberDictionary>(elements->arguments()), isolate);
5312  arguments = NumberDictionary::Add(isolate, arguments, entry.as_uint32(),
5313  value, details);
5314  // If the attributes were NONE, we would have called set rather than
5315  // reconfigure.
5316  DCHECK_NE(NONE, attributes);
5317  object->RequireSlowElements(*arguments);
5318  elements->set_arguments(*arguments);
5319  } else {
5320  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> arguments(elements->arguments(), isolate);
5321  DictionaryElementsAccessor::ReconfigureImpl(isolate, object, arguments,
5322  entry.adjust_down(length),
5323  value, attributes);
5324  }
5325  }
5326 };
5327 
5328 class FastSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor
5329  : public SloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor<
5330  FastSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor, FastHoleyObjectElementsAccessor,
5331  ElementsKindTraits<FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS>> {
5332  public:
5333  static Handle<Object> ConvertArgumentsStoreResult(
5334  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> parameter_map,
5335  Handle<Object> result) {
5336  DCHECK(!IsAliasedArgumentsEntry(*result));
5337  return result;
5338  }
5339 
5340  static DirectHandle<FixedArray> GetArguments(Isolate* isolate,
5341  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> store) {
5342  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements =
5343  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(store);
5344  return DirectHandle<FixedArray>(elements->arguments(), isolate);
5345  }
5346 
5347  static DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> NormalizeImpl(
5348  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5349  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements) {
5350  DirectHandle<FixedArray> arguments = GetArguments(isolate, *elements);
5351  return FastHoleyObjectElementsAccessor::NormalizeImpl(isolate, object,
5352  arguments);
5353  }
5354 
5355  static DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> NormalizeArgumentsElements(
5356  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5357  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements, InternalIndex* entry) {
5358  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
5359  JSObject::NormalizeElements(isolate, object);
5360  elements->set_arguments(*dictionary);
5361  // kMaxUInt32 indicates that a context mapped element got deleted. In this
5362  // case we only normalize the elements (aka. migrate to SLOW_SLOPPY).
5363  if (entry->is_not_found()) return dictionary;
5364  uint32_t length = elements->length();
5365  if (entry->as_uint32() >= length) {
5366  *entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, entry->as_uint32() - length)
5367  .adjust_up(length);
5368  }
5369  return dictionary;
5370  }
5371 
5372  static void SloppyDeleteImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> obj,
5373  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements,
5374  InternalIndex entry) {
5375  // Always normalize element on deleting an entry.
5376  NormalizeArgumentsElements(isolate, obj, elements, &entry);
5377  SlowSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor::SloppyDeleteImpl(isolate, obj,
5378  elements, entry);
5379  }
5380 
5381  static Maybe<bool> AddImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5382  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
5383  PropertyAttributes attributes,
5384  uint32_t new_capacity) {
5385  DCHECK_EQ(NONE, attributes);
5386  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements(
5387  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(object->elements()), isolate);
5388  DirectHandle<FixedArray> old_arguments(elements->arguments(), isolate);
5389  if (IsNumberDictionary(*old_arguments) ||
5390  static_cast<uint32_t>(old_arguments->length()) < new_capacity) {
5391  MAYBE_RETURN(GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(isolate, object, new_capacity),
5392  Nothing<bool>());
5393  }
5394  Tagged<FixedArray> arguments = elements->arguments();
5395  // For fast holey objects, the entry equals the index. The code above made
5396  // sure that there's enough space to store the value. We cannot convert
5397  // index to entry explicitly since the slot still contains the hole, so the
5398  // current EntryForIndex would indicate that it is "absent" by returning
5399  // kMaxUInt32.
5400  FastHoleyObjectElementsAccessor::SetImpl(arguments, InternalIndex(index),
5401  *value);
5402  return Just(true);
5403  }
5404 
5405  static void ReconfigureImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5406  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> store,
5407  InternalIndex entry, DirectHandle<Object> value,
5408  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
5409  DCHECK_EQ(object->elements(), *store);
5410  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements(
5411  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(*store), isolate);
5412  NormalizeArgumentsElements(isolate, object, elements, &entry);
5413  SlowSloppyArgumentsElementsAccessor::ReconfigureImpl(
5414  isolate, object, store, entry, value, attributes);
5415  }
5416 
5417  static void CopyElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from,
5418  uint32_t from_start, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to,
5419  ElementsKind from_kind, uint32_t to_start,
5420  int packed_size, int copy_size) {
5421  DCHECK(!IsNumberDictionary(to));
5422  if (from_kind == SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS) {
5423  CopyDictionaryToObjectElements(isolate, from, from_start, to,
5424  HOLEY_ELEMENTS, to_start, copy_size);
5425  } else {
5426  DCHECK_EQ(FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS, from_kind);
5427  CopyObjectToObjectElements(isolate, from, HOLEY_ELEMENTS, from_start, to,
5428  HOLEY_ELEMENTS, to_start, copy_size);
5429  }
5430  }
5431 
5432  static Maybe<bool> GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(Isolate* isolate,
5433  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5434  uint32_t capacity) {
5435  DirectHandle<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements(
5436  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(object->elements()), isolate);
5437  DirectHandle<FixedArray> old_arguments(
5438  Cast<FixedArray>(elements->arguments()), isolate);
5439  ElementsKind from_kind = object->GetElementsKind();
5440  // This method should only be called if there's a reason to update the
5441  // elements.
5442  DCHECK(from_kind == SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS ||
5443  static_cast<uint32_t>(old_arguments->length()) < capacity);
5444  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> arguments;
5445  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5446  isolate, arguments,
5447  ConvertElementsWithCapacity(isolate, object, old_arguments, from_kind,
5448  capacity),
5449  Nothing<bool>());
5450  DirectHandle<Map> new_map = JSObject::GetElementsTransitionMap(
5451  isolate, object, FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS);
5452  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
5453  elements->set_arguments(Cast<FixedArray>(*arguments));
5454  JSObject::ValidateElements(isolate, *object);
5455  return Just(true);
5456  }
5457 };
5458 
5459 template <typename Subclass, typename BackingStoreAccessor, typename KindTraits>
5460 class StringWrapperElementsAccessor
5461  : public ElementsAccessorBase<Subclass, KindTraits> {
5462  public:
5463  static Handle<Object> GetInternalImpl(Isolate* isolate,
5464  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder,
5465  InternalIndex entry) {
5466  return GetImpl(isolate, holder, entry);
5467  }
5468 
5469  static Handle<Object> GetImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> holder,
5470  InternalIndex entry) {
5471  DirectHandle<String> string(GetString(*holder), isolate);
5472  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(string->length());
5473  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5474  return isolate->factory()->LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(
5475  String::Flatten(isolate, string)->Get(entry.as_int()));
5476  }
5477  return BackingStoreAccessor::GetImpl(isolate, holder->elements(),
5478  entry.adjust_down(length));
5479  }
5480 
5481  static DirectHandle<Object> GetImpl(Isolate* isolate,
5482  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements,
5483  InternalIndex entry) {
5484  UNREACHABLE();
5485  }
5486 
5487  static PropertyDetails GetDetailsImpl(Tagged<JSObject> holder,
5488  InternalIndex entry) {
5489  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(GetString(holder)->length());
5490  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5491  PropertyAttributes attributes =
5492  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(READ_ONLY | DONT_DELETE);
5493  return PropertyDetails(PropertyKind::kData, attributes,
5494  PropertyCellType::kNoCell);
5495  }
5496  return BackingStoreAccessor::GetDetailsImpl(holder,
5497  entry.adjust_down(length));
5498  }
5499 
5500  static InternalIndex GetEntryForIndexImpl(
5501  Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> holder,
5502  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store, size_t index,
5503  PropertyFilter filter) {
5504  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(GetString(holder)->length());
5505  if (index < length) return InternalIndex(index);
5506  InternalIndex backing_store_entry =
5507  BackingStoreAccessor::GetEntryForIndexImpl(
5508  isolate, holder, backing_store, index, filter);
5509  if (backing_store_entry.is_not_found()) return backing_store_entry;
5510  return backing_store_entry.adjust_up(length);
5511  }
5512 
5513  static void DeleteImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> holder,
5514  InternalIndex entry) {
5515  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(GetString(*holder)->length());
5516  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5517  return; // String contents can't be deleted.
5518  }
5519  BackingStoreAccessor::DeleteImpl(isolate, holder,
5520  entry.adjust_down(length));
5521  }
5522 
5523  static void SetImpl(DirectHandle<JSObject> holder, InternalIndex entry,
5524  Tagged<Object> value) {
5525  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(GetString(*holder)->length());
5526  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5527  return; // String contents are read-only.
5528  }
5529  BackingStoreAccessor::SetImpl(holder->elements(), entry.adjust_down(length),
5530  value);
5531  }
5532 
5533  static Maybe<bool> AddImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5534  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
5535  PropertyAttributes attributes,
5536  uint32_t new_capacity) {
5537  DCHECK(index >= static_cast<uint32_t>(GetString(*object)->length()));
5538  // Explicitly grow fast backing stores if needed. Dictionaries know how to
5539  // extend their capacity themselves.
5540  if (KindTraits::Kind == FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS &&
5541  (object->GetElementsKind() == SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS ||
5542  BackingStoreAccessor::GetCapacityImpl(*object, object->elements()) !=
5543  new_capacity)) {
5544  MAYBE_RETURN(GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(isolate, object, new_capacity),
5545  Nothing<bool>());
5546  }
5547  BackingStoreAccessor::AddImpl(isolate, object, index, value, attributes,
5548  new_capacity);
5549  return Just(true);
5550  }
5551 
5552  static void ReconfigureImpl(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5553  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> store,
5554  InternalIndex entry, DirectHandle<Object> value,
5555  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
5556  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(GetString(*object)->length());
5557  if (entry.as_uint32() < length) {
5558  return; // String contents can't be reconfigured.
5559  }
5560  BackingStoreAccessor::ReconfigureImpl(
5561  isolate, object, store, entry.adjust_down(length), value, attributes);
5562  }
5563 
5564  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus AddElementsToKeyAccumulatorImpl(
5565  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver, KeyAccumulator* accumulator,
5566  AddKeyConversion convert) {
5567  Isolate* isolate = accumulator->isolate();
5568  DirectHandle<String> string(GetString(*receiver), isolate);
5569  string = String::Flatten(isolate, string);
5570  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(string->length());
5571  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5572  DirectHandle<String> key =
5573  isolate->factory()->LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(
5574  string->Get(i));
5575  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(accumulator->AddKey(key, convert));
5576  }
5577  return BackingStoreAccessor::AddElementsToKeyAccumulatorImpl(
5578  receiver, accumulator, convert);
5579  }
5580 
5581  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static ExceptionStatus CollectElementIndicesImpl(
5582  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> backing_store,
5583  KeyAccumulator* keys) {
5584  uint32_t length = GetString(*object)->length();
5585  Factory* factory = keys->isolate()->factory();
5586  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5587  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL(
5588  keys->AddKey(factory->NewNumberFromUint(i)));
5589  }
5590  return BackingStoreAccessor::CollectElementIndicesImpl(object,
5591  backing_store, keys);
5592  }
5593 
5594  static Maybe<bool> GrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(Isolate* isolate,
5595  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5596  uint32_t capacity) {
5597  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> old_elements(object->elements(), isolate);
5598  ElementsKind from_kind = object->GetElementsKind();
5599  if (from_kind == FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS) {
5600  // The optimizing compiler relies on the prototype lookups of String
5601  // objects always returning undefined. If there's a store to the
5602  // initial String.prototype object, make sure all the optimizations
5603  // are invalidated.
5604  isolate->UpdateNoElementsProtectorOnSetLength(object);
5605  }
5606  // This method should only be called if there's a reason to update the
5607  // elements.
5608  DCHECK(from_kind == SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS ||
5609  static_cast<uint32_t>(old_elements->length()) < capacity);
5610  return Subclass::BasicGrowCapacityAndConvertImpl(
5611  isolate, object, old_elements, from_kind, FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS,
5612  capacity);
5613  }
5614 
5615  static void CopyElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> from,
5616  uint32_t from_start, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> to,
5617  ElementsKind from_kind, uint32_t to_start,
5618  int packed_size, int copy_size) {
5619  DCHECK(!IsNumberDictionary(to));
5620  if (from_kind == SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS) {
5621  CopyDictionaryToObjectElements(isolate, from, from_start, to,
5622  HOLEY_ELEMENTS, to_start, copy_size);
5623  } else {
5624  DCHECK_EQ(FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS, from_kind);
5625  CopyObjectToObjectElements(isolate, from, HOLEY_ELEMENTS, from_start, to,
5626  HOLEY_ELEMENTS, to_start, copy_size);
5627  }
5628  }
5629 
5630  static uint32_t NumberOfElementsImpl(Isolate* isolate,
5631  Tagged<JSObject> object,
5632  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> backing_store) {
5633  uint32_t length = GetString(object)->length();
5634  return length + BackingStoreAccessor::NumberOfElementsImpl(isolate, object,
5635  backing_store);
5636  }
5637 
5638  private:
5639  static Tagged<String> GetString(Tagged<JSObject> holder) {
5640  DCHECK(IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(holder));
5641  Tagged<JSPrimitiveWrapper> js_value = Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(holder);
5642  DCHECK(IsString(js_value->value()));
5643  return Cast<String>(js_value->value());
5644  }
5645 };

5673 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> ArrayConstructInitializeElements(
5674  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSArray> array, JavaScriptArguments* args) {
5675  if (args->length() == 0) {
5676  // Optimize the case where there are no parameters passed.
5677  JSArray::Initialize(isolate, array, JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements);
5678  return array;
5679 
5680  } else if (args->length() == 1 && IsNumber(*args->at(0))) {
5681  uint32_t length;
5682  if (!Object::ToArrayLength(*args->at(0), &length)) {
5683  return ThrowArrayLengthRangeError(isolate);
5684  }
5685 
5686  // Optimize the case where there is one argument and the argument is a small
5687  // smi.
5688  if (length > 0 && length < JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray) {
5689  ElementsKind elements_kind = array->GetElementsKind();
5690  JSArray::Initialize(isolate, array, length, length);
5691 
5692  if (!IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
5693  elements_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind);
5694  JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(isolate, array, elements_kind);
5695  }
5696  } else if (length == 0) {
5697  JSArray::Initialize(isolate, array, JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements);
5698  } else {
5699  // Take the argument as the length.
5700  JSArray::Initialize(isolate, array, 0);
5701  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(JSArray::SetLength(isolate, array, length));
5702  }
5703  return array;
5704  }
5705 
5706  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
5707 
5708  // Set length and elements on the array.
5709  int number_of_elements = args->length();
5710  JSObject::EnsureCanContainElements(isolate, array, args, number_of_elements,
5711  ALLOW_CONVERTED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
5712 
5713  // Allocate an appropriately typed elements array.
5714  ElementsKind elements_kind = array->GetElementsKind();
5715  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elms;
5716  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
5717  elms =
5718  Cast<FixedArrayBase>(factory->NewFixedDoubleArray(number_of_elements));
5719  } else {
5720  elms = Cast<FixedArrayBase>(
5721  factory->NewFixedArrayWithHoles(number_of_elements));
5722  }
5723 
5724  // Fill in the content
5725  switch (elements_kind) {
5726  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
5727  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS: {
5728  auto smi_elms = Cast<FixedArray>(elms);
5729  for (int entry = 0; entry < number_of_elements; entry++) {
5730  smi_elms->set(entry, (*args)[entry], SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5731  }
5732  break;
5733  }
5734  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
5735  case PACKED_ELEMENTS: {
5736  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5737  WriteBarrierMode mode = elms->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
5738  auto object_elms = Cast<FixedArray>(elms);
5739  for (int entry = 0; entry < number_of_elements; entry++) {
5740  object_elms->set(entry, (*args)[entry], mode);
5741  }
5742  break;
5743  }
5744  case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
5745 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
5746  {
5747  auto double_elms = Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(elms);
5748  for (int entry = 0; entry < number_of_elements; entry++) {
5749  Tagged<Object> obj = (*args)[entry];
5750  if (Is<Undefined>(obj)) {
5751  double_elms->set_undefined(entry);
5752  } else {
5753  double_elms->set(entry, Object::NumberValue((*args)[entry]));
5754  }
5755  }
5756  break;
5757  }
5758 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
5759  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
5760  auto double_elms = Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(elms);
5761  for (int entry = 0; entry < number_of_elements; entry++) {
5762  double_elms->set(entry, Object::NumberValue((*args)[entry]));
5763  }
5764  break;
5765  }
5766  default:
5767  UNREACHABLE();
5768  }
5769 
5770  array->set_elements(*elms);
5771  array->set_length(Smi::FromInt(number_of_elements));
5772  return array;
5773 }
5774 
5775 void CopyFastNumberJSArrayElementsToTypedArray(Address raw_context,
5776  Address raw_source,
5777  Address raw_destination,
5778  uintptr_t length,
5779  uintptr_t offset) {
5780  Tagged<Context> context = Cast<Context>(Tagged<Object>(raw_context));
5781  Tagged<JSArray> source = Cast<JSArray>(Tagged<Object>(raw_source));
5782  Tagged<JSTypedArray> destination =
5783  Cast<JSTypedArray>(Tagged<Object>(raw_destination));
5784 
5785  switch (destination->GetElementsKind()) {
5786 #define TYPED_ARRAYS_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
5787  case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: \
5788  CHECK(Type##ElementsAccessor::TryCopyElementsFastNumber( \
5789  context, source, destination, length, offset)); \
5790  break;
5791  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAYS_CASE)
5792  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAYS_CASE)
5793 #undef TYPED_ARRAYS_CASE
5794  default:
5795  UNREACHABLE();
5796  }
5797 }
5798 
5799 void CopyTypedArrayElementsToTypedArray(Address raw_source,
5800  Address raw_destination,
5801  uintptr_t length, uintptr_t offset) {
5802  Tagged<JSTypedArray> source = Cast<JSTypedArray>(Tagged<Object>(raw_source));
5803  Tagged<JSTypedArray> destination =
5804  Cast<JSTypedArray>(Tagged<Object>(raw_destination));
5805 
5806  switch (destination->GetElementsKind()) {
5807 #define TYPED_ARRAYS_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
5808  case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: \
5809  Type##ElementsAccessor::CopyElementsFromTypedArray(source, destination, \
5810  length, offset); \
5811  break;
5812  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAYS_CASE)
5813  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAYS_CASE)
5814 #undef TYPED_ARRAYS_CASE
5815  default:
5816  UNREACHABLE();
5817  }
5818 }

5820 void CopyTypedArrayElementsSlice(Address raw_source, Address raw_destination,
5821  uintptr_t start, uintptr_t end) {
5822  Tagged<JSTypedArray> source = Cast<JSTypedArray>(Tagged<Object>(raw_source));
5823  Tagged<JSTypedArray> destination =
5824  Cast<JSTypedArray>(Tagged<Object>(raw_destination));

5826  destination->GetElementsAccessor()->CopyTypedArrayElementsSlice(
5827  source, destination, start, end);

5830 template <typename Mapping>
5831 constexpr bool IsIdentityMapping(const Mapping& mapping, size_t index) {
5832  return (index >= std::size(mapping)) ||
5833  (mapping[index] == index && IsIdentityMapping(mapping, index + 1));
5834 }
5835 
5836 void ElementsAccessor::InitializeOncePerProcess() {
5837  // Here we create an array with more entries than element kinds.
5838  // This is due to the sandbox: this array is indexed with an ElementsKind
5839  // read directly from within the sandbox, which must therefore be considered
5840  // attacker-controlled. An ElementsKind is a uint8_t under the hood, so we
5841  // can either use an array with 256 entries or have an explicit bounds-check
5842  // on access. The latter is probably more expensive.
5843  static_assert(std::is_same_v<std::underlying_type_t<ElementsKind>, uint8_t>);
5844  static ElementsAccessor* accessor_array[256] = {
5845 #define ACCESSOR_ARRAY(Class, Kind, Store) new Class(),
5846  ELEMENTS_LIST(ACCESSOR_ARRAY)
5847 #undef ACCESSOR_ARRAY
5848  };
5849 
5850  static_assert((sizeof(accessor_array) / sizeof(*accessor_array)) >=
5851  kElementsKindCount);
5852 
5853  // Check that the ELEMENTS_LIST macro is in the same order as the ElementsKind
5854  // enum.
5855  constexpr ElementsKind elements_kinds_from_macro[] = {
5856 #define ACCESSOR_KIND(Class, Kind, Store) Kind,
5857  ELEMENTS_LIST(ACCESSOR_KIND)
5858 #undef ACCESSOR_KIND
5859  };
5860  static_assert(IsIdentityMapping(elements_kinds_from_macro, 0));
5861 
5862  elements_accessors_ = accessor_array;
5863 }
5864 
5865 void ElementsAccessor::TearDown() {
5866  if (elements_accessors_ == nullptr) return;
5867 #define ACCESSOR_DELETE(Class, Kind, Store) delete elements_accessors_[Kind];
5868  ELEMENTS_LIST(ACCESSOR_DELETE)
5869 #undef ACCESSOR_DELETE
5870  elements_accessors_ = nullptr;
5871 }
5872 
5873 DirectHandle<JSArray> ElementsAccessor::Concat(Isolate* isolate,
5874  BuiltinArguments* args,
5875  uint32_t concat_size,
5876  uint32_t result_len) {
5877  ElementsKind result_elements_kind = GetInitialFastElementsKind();
5878  bool has_raw_doubles = false;
5879  {
5880  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5881  bool is_holey = false;
5882  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < concat_size; i++) {
5883  Tagged<Object> arg = (*args)[i];
5884  ElementsKind arg_kind = Cast<JSArray>(arg)->GetElementsKind();
5885  has_raw_doubles = has_raw_doubles || IsDoubleElementsKind(arg_kind);
5886  is_holey = is_holey || IsHoleyElementsKind(arg_kind);
5887  result_elements_kind =
5888  GetMoreGeneralElementsKind(result_elements_kind, arg_kind);
5889  }
5890  if (is_holey) {
5891  result_elements_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(result_elements_kind);
5892  }
5893  }
5894 
5895  // If a double array is concatted into a fast elements array, the fast
5896  // elements array needs to be initialized to contain proper holes, since
5897  // boxing doubles may cause incremental marking.
5898  bool requires_double_boxing =
5899  has_raw_doubles && !IsDoubleElementsKind(result_elements_kind);
5900  auto mode =
5901  requires_double_boxing
5902  ? ArrayStorageAllocationMode::INITIALIZE_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_WITH_HOLE
5903  : ArrayStorageAllocationMode::DONT_INITIALIZE_ARRAY_ELEMENTS;
5904  DirectHandle<JSArray> result_array = isolate->factory()->NewJSArray(
5905  result_elements_kind, result_len, result_len, mode);
5906  if (result_len == 0) return result_array;
5907 
5908  uint32_t insertion_index = 0;
5909  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> storage(result_array->elements(), isolate);
5910  ElementsAccessor* accessor = ElementsAccessor::ForKind(result_elements_kind);
5911  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < concat_size; i++) {
5912  // It is crucial to keep |array| in a raw pointer form to avoid
5913  // performance degradation.
5914  Tagged<JSArray> array = Cast<JSArray>((*args)[i]);
5915  uint32_t len = 0;
5916  Object::ToArrayLength(array->length(), &len);
5917  if (len == 0) continue;
5918  ElementsKind from_kind = array->GetElementsKind();
5919  accessor->CopyElements(isolate, array, 0, from_kind, storage,
5920  insertion_index, len);
5921  insertion_index += len;
5922  }
5923 
5924  DCHECK_EQ(insertion_index, result_len);
5925  return result_array;
5926 }
5927

5931 #undef RETURN_NOTHING_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL
5932 #undef RETURN_FAILURE_IF_NOT_SUCCESSFUL
5933 } // namespace internal
